WEBVTT

00:04.655 --> 00:06.275
Richard:
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL SATURDAY,

00:06.275 --> 00:08.172
AND YOU WOULDN'T KNOW
IT'S WINTER HERE IN DALLAS,

00:08.172 --> 00:10.172
AND THE BOYS HAVE THE DAY OFF,
SO I TOLD THE GUYS,

00:10.172 --> 00:12.172
"LET'S DRAG OUT THE MOTOR
SCOOTERS AND GO FOR A RIDE."

00:14.931 --> 00:16.172
[ HORN HONKS ]

00:16.172 --> 00:17.413
[ LAUGHS ]

00:17.413 --> 00:19.896
HEY, FELLAS, I WANT TO
CHECK SOMETHING OUT.

00:19.896 --> 00:21.241
TURNING LEFT.

00:21.241 --> 00:22.931
HEY, BASS' DOOR IS OPEN.

00:22.931 --> 00:25.172
LET'S GO SEE WHAT HE'S DOING
ON A SATURDAY.

00:29.344 --> 00:31.103
YEAH, BUDDY.
IT'S SATURDAY, MAN.

00:31.103 --> 00:32.517
YOUR DOORS ARE OPEN.
WHAT'S UP?

00:32.517 --> 00:34.172
YOU KNOW I COME HERE
TO GET AWAY FROM YOU, RIGHT?

00:34.172 --> 00:36.000
AND THEN YOU SHOW UP
WHEN I'M HERE.

00:38.344 --> 00:39.586
WHOO!

00:39.586 --> 00:41.000
Narrator:
RIGHT NOW ON "FAST N' LOUD"...

00:41.000 --> 00:42.206
BOOM!
WHOO!

00:42.206 --> 00:43.482
Narrator: ...HOT ROD HUNTER
RICHARD RAWLINGS

00:43.482 --> 00:45.655
AND HIS BAND OF MONKEYS
ARE MOVING AND SHAKING...

00:45.655 --> 00:48.551
Man: I THINK HE HAS ANTS
IN HIS PANTS.

00:48.551 --> 00:52.275
...AS THEY BRING THE HEAT
REVIVING A '33 FORD MODEL B...

00:52.275 --> 00:55.206
Mike: YOU'RE ROASTING
MARSHMALLOWS OVER HERE.

00:55.206 --> 00:58.448
...TRYING TO TURN IT INTO
THE PERFECT VINTAGE SHOP TRUCK.

00:58.448 --> 00:59.965
I WAS JUST ABOUT READY TO PUT
THIS THING BACK TOGETHER,

00:59.965 --> 01:01.413
AND NOW I CAN'T.

01:01.413 --> 01:02.517
I'M SCARED IT'S EVEN
GONNA RUN NOW.

01:02.517 --> 01:03.620
Narrator: AND THEN...

01:03.620 --> 01:05.206
WHAT'S THAT?
THAT'S MY 'CUDA.

01:05.206 --> 01:08.275
RICHARD REELS IN A '72
PLYMOUTH 'CUDA...

01:08.275 --> 01:10.655
IF YOU HAD THIS CAR IN 1970,
YOU WERE A BAD DUDE.

01:10.655 --> 01:13.827
...AND GOES ALL IN ON MONSTER
HORSEPOWER FOR THE RIVIERA.

01:13.827 --> 01:16.379
...TO SEE WHERE THE MONSTER
POWER IS CREATED.

01:16.379 --> 01:17.827
Jason: HERE'S YOUR ENGINE
FOR THE RIVIERA.

01:17.827 --> 01:21.206
700.
800 HORSEPOWER.

01:21.206 --> 01:22.413
HA HA!

01:22.413 --> 01:26.068
[ LAUGHING ]

01:26.068 --> 01:27.103
Brian:
YEAH, YOU KNOW ME.

01:27.103 --> 01:29.034
I GOT A LOT OF STUFF TO DO,
BUSY MAN.

01:29.034 --> 01:31.000
DON'T TAKE THAT OFF.
I LIKE IT BETTER WITH IT ON.

01:31.000 --> 01:32.551
IT'S A LOT BETTER LOOK
FOR YOU. [BLEEP]

01:32.551 --> 01:34.172
DUDE, I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DO
FIVE DAYS AT THE MONKEY

01:34.172 --> 01:36.137
AND THEN COME HERE
AND GET AFTER IT ALL WEEKEND.

01:36.137 --> 01:37.379
Jason:
WELL, LOOK AT THIS PLACE.

01:37.379 --> 01:39.068
YOU GOT A LOT OF STUFF
CRAMMED IN THIS SHOP.

01:39.068 --> 01:40.586
YEAH, I KNOW.
I HAVE SO MUCH STUFF IN HERE.

01:40.586 --> 01:41.862
GOD, HOW MANY CARS
YOU GOT IN HERE?

01:41.862 --> 01:43.448
-LIKE FIVE.
-IS THAT ALL?

01:43.448 --> 01:45.103
-YEAH, THAT'S ALL, JUST FIVE.
-HOW DO YOU WORK IN HERE?

01:45.103 --> 01:46.724
IT'S ALL BOXED IN, MAN.
GOOD GOD.

01:46.724 --> 01:48.517
WELL, THERE'S ONLY
JUST ME IN HERE.

01:48.517 --> 01:49.551
IT'S NOT, LIKE, A CREW.

01:49.551 --> 01:50.896
Richard:
BRIAN BASS AND I GO WAY BACK,

01:50.896 --> 01:52.931
BUT NONE OF THESE GUYS
HAVE SEEN HIS SHOP BEFORE.

01:52.931 --> 01:55.000
I'VE BEEN COMING DOWN HERE
FOR 13, 14 YEARS.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.758
BASS HAS GOT, LIKE,
IN THE NOOKS AND CRANNIES,

01:56.758 --> 01:58.275
GOT SOME OF THE COOLEST
[BLEEP] YOU'LL EVER FIND

01:58.275 --> 01:59.344
IN AN AUTO SHOP.

01:59.344 --> 02:00.896
IF YOU NEED IT,
IT'S PROBABLY HERE.

02:00.896 --> 02:02.758
THIS PLACE IS EITHER
A HOT RODDER'S HEAVEN

02:02.758 --> 02:04.068
OR A CANDIDATE
FOR "HOARDERS."

02:04.068 --> 02:05.620
Charles: IS THE STUFF CLOSE
TO THE TRASH

02:05.620 --> 02:06.655
CAN GONNA GO IN THE TRASH
CAN EVENTUALLY, OR...

02:06.655 --> 02:07.758
I'M JUST CURIOUS.

02:07.758 --> 02:08.689
Brian:
IT DEPENDS ON WHAT IT IS.

02:08.689 --> 02:09.896
SOME OF THAT STUFF IS IMPORTANT.

02:09.896 --> 02:11.793
I DO LOOK LIKE A LITTLE BIT
OF A HOARDER,

02:11.793 --> 02:13.448
BUT HONESTLY, EVERYTHING
IN THERE HAS A PURPOSE.

02:13.448 --> 02:14.793
IT'S ALL HOT-ROD PARTS.

02:14.793 --> 02:16.103
THIS IS THE LATEST THING
I'VE WORKED ON.

02:16.103 --> 02:18.000
-WHAT IS THAT?
-THIS IS A '25 MODEL T ROADSTER

02:18.000 --> 02:20.758
THAT I'VE BEEN BUILDING
FOR THAT BEACH RACE,

02:20.758 --> 02:22.034
THE RACE OF GENTLEMEN.

02:22.034 --> 02:24.448
SO IT'S GOT A SUPERCHARGED
FLATHEAD.

02:24.448 --> 02:25.793
-WOW.
-DANG, THAT'S BAD.

02:25.793 --> 02:27.517
-THAT'S PRETTY SWEET.
-THAT IS FREAKING COOL.

02:27.517 --> 02:28.965
Richard:
WHAT KIND OF TOP SPEEDS
YOU THINK YOU'RE GONNA GET?

02:28.965 --> 02:30.275
Brian:
AW, MAN, I DON'T KNOW.

02:30.275 --> 02:31.275
IT'S PROBABLY GONNA BE
FAST ENOUGH

02:31.275 --> 02:32.689
THAT I HAVE TO WEAR A HELMET.

02:32.689 --> 02:34.172
-BOOM.
-LOOK AT THAT.

02:34.172 --> 02:35.862
-ASK, AND YOU SHALL RECEIVE.
-YEAH, WHY WON'T YOU?

02:35.862 --> 02:37.724
THIS IS A SWEET CAR.
DID I USED TO OWN THIS?

02:37.724 --> 02:39.103
Brian: I DON'T THINK SO.

02:39.103 --> 02:40.655
THAT CAR CAME OUT OF
A COLLECTION OUT OF EAST TEXAS.

02:40.655 --> 02:42.172
SURE LOOKS LIKE
WHAT I USED TO OWN.

02:42.172 --> 02:43.206
WHAT'S UP
WITH THE LITTLE TRUCK?

02:43.206 --> 02:44.448
THIS IS, WHAT, A '34?

02:44.448 --> 02:45.965
THIS IS A '33 FORD PICKUP.

02:45.965 --> 02:48.206
I ACTUALLY DRUG THIS
OUT OF A BARN DOWN IN WACO

02:48.206 --> 02:50.000
ABOUT 2 YEARS AGO.
-NO KIDDING.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.793
I BOUGHT IT FOR MYSELF
JUST TO BUILD AS A SHOP TRUCK,

02:51.793 --> 02:53.275
BUT IT'S BEEN
ON THE BACK BURNER

02:53.275 --> 02:54.758
LIKE EVERYTHING ELSE
OF MY OWN.

02:54.758 --> 02:56.206
IT WAS AN OLD
SERVICE-STATION TRUCK,

02:56.206 --> 02:57.689
THE ONE WITH THE DINOSAUR.
-SINCLAIR.

02:57.689 --> 02:58.965
YEAH, SO IT
WAS THAT COLOR GREEN,

02:58.965 --> 03:00.482
AND IT JUST FADED
THROUGH THE YEARS,

03:00.482 --> 03:01.827
AND, YOU KNOW, LIKE,
THAT PATINA

03:01.827 --> 03:03.172
CANNOT BE RE-CREATED
VERY EASILY,

03:03.172 --> 03:04.689
SO I WOULD RATHER JUST...

03:04.689 --> 03:06.137
WELL, EXCEPT FOR MIKE.
MIKE COULD PROBABLY DO IT.

03:06.137 --> 03:07.620
WELL, I WAS GONNA SAY,
"WATCH YOUR TONGUE."

03:07.620 --> 03:08.827
BUT FOR ME, IT WOULD BE
TOUGH TO RE-CREATE.

03:08.827 --> 03:10.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

03:10.000 --> 03:11.206
WOULD YOU GO FLATHEAD
OR SMALL-BLOCK?

03:11.206 --> 03:12.586
WELL, I WANTED TO PUT
A FLATHEAD IN IT,

03:12.586 --> 03:13.827
BUT I DON'T REALLY HAVE
A GOOD ONE RIGHT NOW.

03:13.827 --> 03:16.275
Brian: THIS IS A 1934
FORD MODEL B PICKUP,

03:16.275 --> 03:17.724
AND THAT MEANS IT HAS
A FOUR-CYLINDER IN IT.

03:17.724 --> 03:19.137
NOW, TO BUILD A HOT ROD,

03:19.137 --> 03:20.310
YOU KIND OF WANT TO GET RID OF
THAT FOUR-CYLINDER,

03:20.310 --> 03:21.862
SO HONESTLY,
IF I WAS GONNA DO IT,

03:21.862 --> 03:24.103
I WOULD PULL THE 4-CYLINDER OUT
AND PUT A FLATHEAD V-8 IN IT.

03:24.103 --> 03:26.862
I THINK THAT'S THE WAY TO GO.

03:26.862 --> 03:29.137
Richard: THE '33 MODEL B IS
A HOT RODDER'S FAVORITE.

03:29.137 --> 03:31.448
THEY'VE BEEN BUILT IN JUST ABOUT
EVERY WAY YOU CAN IMAGINE,

03:31.448 --> 03:33.241
AND FOR THIS ONE,
THE BIGGEST BANG FOR THE BUCK

03:33.241 --> 03:34.689
WOULD BE NOT TO OVERDO IT

03:34.689 --> 03:37.896
AND MAKE IT INTO JUST
A SUPER COOL SHOP TRUCK,

03:37.896 --> 03:39.931
WHICH MEANS WE'D USE IT
AT THE GARAGE TO LOOK GOOD

03:39.931 --> 03:41.482
WHEN WE'RE PICKING UP PARTS
AND RUNNING ERRANDS,

03:41.482 --> 03:43.482
AND AT THE SAME TIME,
IT'D STILL BE A KICK-ASS,

03:43.482 --> 03:45.137
ORIGINAL GAS MONKEY HOT ROD.

03:45.137 --> 03:46.241
AND IF YOU HAPPEN TO OWN
A BUSINESS

03:46.241 --> 03:48.000
AND IN NEED OF A SHOP TRUCK,
WELL,

03:48.000 --> 03:49.655
I'D EVEN BE WILLING TO PART
WITH IT FOR THE RIGHT PRICE.

03:49.655 --> 03:51.793
I JUST DON'T HAVE TIME TO WORK
ON THIS THING, MAN.

03:51.793 --> 03:54.724
I WOULD LOVE TO DO A DROPPED
AXLE, HYDRAULIC BRAKES,

03:54.724 --> 03:56.103
LEAVE THE PATINA AS IS,
YOU KNOW,

03:56.103 --> 03:57.896
AND JUST BUILD
A NICE CHASSIS,

03:57.896 --> 03:59.241
SO I COULD DRIVE IT, YOU KNOW,
AS A SHOP TRUCK, BUT...

03:59.241 --> 04:00.517
PROBABLY PUT A WINDSHIELD
IN IT, RIGHT?

04:00.517 --> 04:02.689
YEAH, WELL...

04:02.689 --> 04:04.758
THIS THING IS PRETTY SWEET,
AND YOU KNOW I LIKE GREEN.

04:04.758 --> 04:06.000
-YEAH.
-UH-OH.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.620
I'VE KNOWN RICHARD
FOR A LONG TIME,

04:07.620 --> 04:09.344
AND I CAN TELL WHEN HE'S REALLY
GETTING JAZZED ABOUT SOMETHING.

04:09.344 --> 04:10.827
LOOK AT THIS
AIR CONDITIONING.

04:10.827 --> 04:11.965
WSHEWW!

04:11.965 --> 04:13.275
IT'S GETTING
COOLER ALREADY.

04:13.275 --> 04:14.827
I CAN SEE THE TWINKLE
IN HIS EYE.

04:14.827 --> 04:16.413
HE WAS INTO THIS TRUCK.

04:16.413 --> 04:17.724
YOU OUGHT
TO SELL ME THIS.

04:17.724 --> 04:19.275
DUDE, I REALLY BOUGHT
THIS THING FOR MYSELF.

04:19.275 --> 04:20.655
I WASN'T REALLY PLANNING
ON SELLING IT.

04:20.655 --> 04:22.344
WELL, YOU SAID YOU WANTED
TO BUILD IT, SO...

04:22.344 --> 04:23.827
YEAH, I DO WANT TO BUILD IT,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

04:23.827 --> 04:26.275
OBVIOUSLY IT'S, LIKE,
LAST ON MY LIST RIGHT NOW.

04:26.275 --> 04:27.310
THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.
LOOK AROUND.

04:27.310 --> 04:28.689
YEAH.

04:28.689 --> 04:29.965
SO IF YOU SELL IT TO ME,
YOU GET TO BUILD IT.

04:29.965 --> 04:31.448
DUDE, I DIG IT.
WHAT'S THE NUMBER?

04:31.448 --> 04:33.344
THAT'S NOT SOMETHING YOU
JUST GO FIND EVERYWHERE.

04:33.344 --> 04:34.517
IT TOOK ME A WHILE
TO FIND THIS TRUCK,

04:34.517 --> 04:35.620
SO IT'S NOT GOING
TO BE CHEAP.

04:35.620 --> 04:37.241
WELL, HERE'S
THE TRICKY TRICK.

04:37.241 --> 04:39.965
I'VE GOT AN H&H FLATHEAD,
ALL BUILT, IN THE BOX.

04:39.965 --> 04:41.448
WELL, THAT'D BOLT
RIGHT IN THERE, JUST ABOUT.

04:41.448 --> 04:42.413
MM-HMM.

04:42.413 --> 04:43.413
POP THAT STRAP, BUD.

04:43.413 --> 04:45.034
Richard:
Y'ALL REMEMBER A WHILE BACK,

04:45.034 --> 04:46.620
I DID SOME LATE-NIGHT SHOPPING

04:46.620 --> 04:48.758
AND ACCIDENTALLY, ON PURPOSE,
ENDED UP WITH A FLATHEAD MOTOR.

04:48.758 --> 04:52.241
MAN, I KNOW I HAD A COUPLE BEERS
LAST NIGHT, BUT NO WAY.

04:52.241 --> 04:54.172
CHECK THAT BABY OUT.

04:54.172 --> 04:55.379
HOW MUCH DO YOU WANT
FOR THIS STUFF?

04:55.379 --> 04:56.793
$8,500.

04:56.793 --> 04:58.172
YOU SAID I'LL HAVE 8,500 CASH
WHEN YOU GET HERE.

04:58.172 --> 04:59.724
Tony: I PROBABLY WOULD HAVE GOT
IT FOR LESS THAN THAT

04:59.724 --> 05:01.448
IF I WAS HANDLING THE DEAL
ON THE INTERNET, BUT...

05:01.448 --> 05:02.793
SHUT UP, TONY.

05:02.793 --> 05:04.068
Richard: I ALWAYS KNEW IT WAS
JUST A MATTER OF TIME

05:04.068 --> 05:05.551
BEFORE I'D HAVE
A GOOD USE FOR IT.

05:05.551 --> 05:07.379
WELL, IF I MAKE THE RIGHT
DEAL WITH BRIAN,

05:07.379 --> 05:08.448
THAT TIME COULD BE NOW.

05:08.448 --> 05:11.793
I'M THINKING $15,000.

05:11.793 --> 05:13.689
$15,000?

05:13.689 --> 05:15.275
BASS HIT ME AT $15,000,

05:15.275 --> 05:17.517
AND I KNEW THAT I WAS NOT GONNA
GET HIM TO MOVE AN INCH.

05:17.517 --> 05:20.172
I KIND OF FEEL LIKE HE MIGHT BE
CHARGING ME 1,000 PER YEAR

05:20.172 --> 05:22.034
OF KNOWING ME
AND PUTTING UP WITH ME.

05:22.034 --> 05:23.620
MAYBE THAT'S WHERE HE CAME UP
WITH THE NUMBER.

05:23.620 --> 05:25.103
I KNOW I'M NOT GONNA
GET YOU OFF $15,000.

05:25.103 --> 05:26.137
NO.

05:26.137 --> 05:27.172
I DON'T HAVE TO SELL IT,

05:27.172 --> 05:28.310
AND IT'S A SELLER'S
MARKET RIGHT NOW.

05:32.034 --> 05:32.965
ALL RIGHT.
[BLEEP] IT.

05:32.965 --> 05:34.310
LET'S DO IT.
-HEY.

05:34.310 --> 05:36.482
GOD, THAT WAS THE EASIEST
NEGOTIATION I'VE EVER SEEN.

05:36.482 --> 05:37.724
HELL YEAH.

05:37.724 --> 05:38.862
PLUS IT'S, LIKE,
THE FIRST THING

05:38.862 --> 05:39.827
I'VE EVER BOUGHT OUT
OF THIS SHOP.

05:39.827 --> 05:41.068
IF I'M GONNA SELL THIS TRUCK,

05:41.068 --> 05:42.448
I'D MUCH RATHER SELL IT
TO RICHARD

05:42.448 --> 05:43.758
AND GET TO BE ON BOARD
BUILDING IT THAN ANYTHING ELSE.

05:43.758 --> 05:45.103
I MEAN, THAT'S REALLY
THE IDEAL SITUATION --

05:45.103 --> 05:46.551
SELL IT TO HIM,
COLLECT THAT MONEY

05:46.551 --> 05:48.206
AND THEN COLLECT MORE MONEY
FOR BUILDING IT?

05:48.206 --> 05:49.793
DUDE, THAT'S A NO-BRAINER.

05:49.793 --> 05:51.206
WHAT DO WE GOT TO DO?
DO WE GOT TO PULL
IT OFF THE FRAME?

05:51.206 --> 05:52.689
-I CAN TELL YOU WHAT I WOULD DO.
-OKAY.

05:52.689 --> 05:54.862
I WOULD PULL IT ALL APART,
GET IT DOWN TO A BARE FRAME,

05:54.862 --> 05:57.482
DO A DROPPED AXLE IN THE FRONT,
DO A STOCK REAR END

05:57.482 --> 06:00.103
BUT WITH DIFFERENT GEARS,
DO A NEWER TRANSMISSION

06:00.103 --> 06:01.551
AND THEN DO A REALLY
NICE INTERIOR,

06:01.551 --> 06:03.379
PAINT THE FIREWALL
AND PUT YOUR FLATHEAD IN IT.

06:03.379 --> 06:05.448
ARE WE PAINTING THE CHASSIS,
TOO, WHILE WE GOT IT OUT?

06:05.448 --> 06:06.931
I WOULD PAINT
THE CHASSIS.

06:06.931 --> 06:08.827
I WOULD JUST PICK A GREEN
IN THIS GENERAL AREA HERE

06:08.827 --> 06:11.379
AND PAINT
THE CHASSIS THAT COLOR.

06:11.379 --> 06:13.137
Richard: HERE'S THE PLAN --
WE'LL TAKE THIS FORD MODEL B

06:13.137 --> 06:15.034
AND MAKE IT INTO
A VINTAGE-LOOKING SHOP TRUCK,

06:15.034 --> 06:17.172
READY TO RUN PARTS
OR JUST LOOKING COOL.

06:17.172 --> 06:18.620
WE'LL KEEP THE 85 YEARS
OF PATINA,

06:18.620 --> 06:20.310
BUT UPGRADE JUST ABOUT
EVERYTHING ELSE.

06:20.310 --> 06:23.137
PUT A MODERN SUSPENSION
UNDER IT, REDO THE INTERIOR,

06:23.137 --> 06:24.758
GIVE IT SOME POWER
WITH A FLATHEAD V-8

06:24.758 --> 06:26.068
THAT I'VE ALREADY PAID FOR,

06:26.068 --> 06:28.000
AND I'LL GIVE THEM
A BUDGET OF $5,000

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
AND 2 WEEKS
TO GO THROUGH IT AND BAM!

06:30.000 --> 06:31.931
THIS COULD BE THE PERFECT
SHOP-TRUCK BUILD.

06:31.931 --> 06:33.379
I'M GONNA CALL MATER
AND HAVE HIM COME GET IT,

06:33.379 --> 06:35.034
SO YOU GOT A LOT OF [BLEEP]
TO MOVE TO GET IT OUT OF HERE.

06:35.034 --> 06:36.517
THAT'S NOT PART
OF THE DEAL.

06:36.517 --> 06:37.862
I THINK THESE GUYS NEED TO
STICK AROUND AND HELP ME.

06:37.862 --> 06:39.034
-OH, NO, NO.
-WE'RE ON MOTORCYCLES, MAN.

06:39.034 --> 06:40.310
-IT'S SATURDAY.
-PEACE OUT ON THAT.

06:40.310 --> 06:41.689
YEAH, WE AIN'T GETTING PAID
FOR THAT.

06:41.689 --> 06:42.931
THIS IS OUR DAY OFF.
YOU SAID YOU WERE WORKING.

06:42.931 --> 06:43.862
-YEAH, WE'RE NOT.
-IT'S SATURDAY.

06:43.862 --> 06:45.000
WHY IS IT
ALWAYS LIKE THIS?

06:45.000 --> 06:46.862
Mike: THAT IS A COOL TRUCK.
IT IS.

06:46.862 --> 06:48.827
IT'S JUST THE WHOLE IDEA
OF MAKING HIM BE A PART

06:48.827 --> 06:51.344
OF THE BUILD OF SOMETHING THAT
HE REALLY WANTED FOR HIMSELF,

06:51.344 --> 06:53.068
BUT I GET TO KEEP IT
AND SELL IT.

06:53.068 --> 06:54.275
MAN, THAT'S MESSED UP.

06:54.275 --> 06:56.137
-YEAH, IT IS MESSED UP.
-IT IS KIND OF FUN.

06:56.137 --> 06:57.551
WHERE TO?

06:57.551 --> 07:01.206
I GUESS EITHER A HOT DOG
OR A PIZZA OR A BURGER.

07:01.206 --> 07:03.758
Brian: NOW WAIT A MINUTE.
WHERE'S MY MONEY?!

07:03.758 --> 07:04.793
RICHARD!

07:04.793 --> 07:06.517
YOU FORGOT TO PAY ME!

07:11.379 --> 07:12.896
Richard:
WITH THE TRUCK ON DECK TO BUILD,

07:12.896 --> 07:14.241
NOW IT'S A GOOD TIME
TO VISIT MOTOWN

07:14.241 --> 07:15.275
AND CHECK IN ON THE MOTOR

07:15.275 --> 07:16.931
THAT WE'RE BUILDING
FOR THE RIVIERA.

07:16.931 --> 07:24.172
♪♪

07:24.172 --> 07:25.586
SO WITH RUSSELL
AND JOSH IN TOW,

07:25.586 --> 07:27.310
WE TOOK OFF ON A LITTLE
ROAD TRIP TO DETROIT

07:27.310 --> 07:29.000
TO CHECK ON THE MOTOR
FOR THE BUICK RIVIERA

07:29.000 --> 07:30.448
THAT WE'RE BUILDING
TO TAKE TO SEMA.

07:30.448 --> 07:32.620
THE '72 RIVIERA IS GONNA BE
THE BIGGEST,

07:32.620 --> 07:35.310
BADDEST CAR WE'VE EVER BUILT,
AND I'M FORKING OUT 300 GRAND

07:35.310 --> 07:38.517
TO MAKE ALL THIS HAPPEN
IN A MATTER OF MONTHS.

07:38.517 --> 07:39.758
KATECH, MAN.
-YEAH, BUDDY.

07:39.758 --> 07:40.689
Richard:
THESE GUYS HAVE BUILT US

07:40.689 --> 07:41.827
A COUPLE MOTORS BEFORE,

07:41.827 --> 07:43.241
BUT THIS IS
OUR FIRST TIME UP HERE.

07:43.241 --> 07:45.793
IT'S GOOD TO SEE WHERE
THE MONSTER POWER IS CREATED.

07:45.793 --> 07:48.448
I WANT 1,000 HORSEPOWER
ON THE GROUND

07:48.448 --> 07:49.758
WITH THE RIVIERA.

07:49.758 --> 07:51.241
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.
-BIG RIVI POWER.

07:51.241 --> 07:52.965
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.
OH, THERE THEY ARE.

07:52.965 --> 07:54.310
HERE WE ARE.

07:54.310 --> 07:56.068
COOL.
FREAKING AWESOME.

07:56.068 --> 07:57.724
-WHERE Y'ALL GOING?
-WE'RE GOING TO KATECH.

07:57.724 --> 07:59.965
ALL RIGHT.
