07:59.965 --> 08:01.931
DUMBASS, GEEZ.
-JUST PARK THAT.

08:01.931 --> 08:03.620
YEAH,
YOU TAKE CARE OF IT.

08:03.620 --> 08:04.724
[BLEEP] GUYS.

08:04.724 --> 08:06.413
NOW I SEE WHY
THEY BROUGHT ME ALONG.

08:06.413 --> 08:08.655
AGE BEFORE BEAUTY.LOOK AT THAT.

08:10.413 --> 08:11.620
Richard: BEFORE TODAY,

08:11.620 --> 08:13.034
THE MONKEYS
GOT BUSY ON THAT OLD LAND YACHT

08:13.034 --> 08:15.103
BY GIVING IT A CHOP
TO BRING OUT MORE OF ITS SEXY

08:15.103 --> 08:16.724
YET AGGRESSIVE CORVETTE
STYLING.

08:16.724 --> 08:17.965
YEAH, THAT'S MUCH BETTER.

08:17.965 --> 08:19.310
NEXT, WE FLEW OUT
TO SACRAMENTO TO VISIT

08:19.310 --> 08:20.793
CHRIS ALSTON'S CHASSISWORKS

08:20.793 --> 08:22.206
TO GET OUR MITTS
ON A CUSTOM FRAME

08:22.206 --> 08:23.793
THAT COULD HANDLE
ALL THOSE HORSES

08:23.793 --> 08:26.931
COMING OUT OF THAT KATECH MOTOR
WE'RE ABOUT TO CHECK OUT.

08:26.931 --> 08:28.344
WELCOME TO KATECH.

08:28.344 --> 08:29.724
MY NAME IS JASON HARDING.

08:29.724 --> 08:31.379
I'M THE DIRECTOR OF AFTERMARKET
OPERATIONS FOR KATECH.

08:31.379 --> 08:33.379
WE DID THE ENGINES
FOR THE SHINER BEER TRUCK

08:33.379 --> 08:35.379
AND A CREW-CUT TRUCK,
AND WE WERE VERY EXCITED

08:35.379 --> 08:37.517
WHEN RICHARD SAID HE NEEDED
AN LT ENGINE

08:37.517 --> 08:40.241
FOR THE NEW RIVIERA PROJECT.

08:40.241 --> 08:41.931
Richard: KATECH IS FAMOUS
FOR BUILDING ENGINES

08:41.931 --> 08:43.413
FOR THE GM CORVETTE TEAM

08:43.413 --> 08:45.862
THAT DOMINATED RACING CIRCUITS
FOR DECADES.

08:45.862 --> 08:47.310
THESE GUYS HAVE EVERYTHING
TO MAKE A MOTOR

08:47.310 --> 08:49.137
THE ABSOLUTE BEST IT CAN BE.

08:49.137 --> 08:51.827
WHEN IT COMES TO MOTORSPORTS
TECHNOLOGY, KATECH IS IT.

08:51.827 --> 08:53.655
Jason: THIS IS OUR
FULL-SERVICE CAR SHOP,

08:53.655 --> 08:56.275
SO THIS IS A SHOP
FULL OF CUSTOMERS' CARS.

08:56.275 --> 08:57.206
THEY BOUGHT A NEW CORVETTE,

08:57.206 --> 08:58.379
NEW CAMARO,
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,

08:58.379 --> 08:59.655
AND THEY WANT
TO GIVE IT MORE POWER

08:59.655 --> 09:01.310
AND SET IT APART
FROM THE REST OF THEM.

09:01.310 --> 09:02.620
THEY SEND IT TO KATECH.

09:02.620 --> 09:03.965
SO YOU'LL YANK IT
AND DO ALL THE WORK

09:03.965 --> 09:04.965
AND PUT IT BACK IN
AND SEND IT BACK TO THEM?

09:04.965 --> 09:06.413
DO IT ALL
IN-HOUSE HERE.

09:06.413 --> 09:08.482
THIS ONE IS WHAT I LIKE
RIGHT HERE.

09:08.482 --> 09:11.379
THIS IS VERY SIMILAR
TO THE WHOLE CONCEPT

09:11.379 --> 09:14.827
I CAME UP WITH THE '72 RIVIERA
BECAUSE THE RIVIERA WAS BUILT

09:14.827 --> 09:16.862
AS A GENTLEMAN'S HOT ROD,
SO IT HAD POWER.

09:16.862 --> 09:18.896
IT HAD TORQUE, BUT IT WASN'T
IN A SMALL PACKAGE.

09:18.896 --> 09:20.206
IT WAS A BIG PACKAGE.

09:20.206 --> 09:22.034
Josh: SEEING THE MOTOR
IN A CORVETTE Z06 IS AWESOME.

09:22.034 --> 09:23.758
IT DOES RESEMBLE
A CORVETTE ACTUALLY.

09:23.758 --> 09:26.448
IT LOOKS VERY SIMILAR TO IT
WITH THE SLOPING BACK LINES,

09:26.448 --> 09:27.862
WITH THE NARROWING IN THE BACK.
-YEAH, THE VENTS.

09:27.862 --> 09:29.379
WE'RE GONNA TRIM
THAT BACK WINDOW IN...

09:29.379 --> 09:31.448
-YEP, YEP.
-...RUN BIG VENTS RIGHT HERE

09:31.448 --> 09:33.241
GETTING DOWN TO THE WHEELS
AND THE BRAKES.

09:33.241 --> 09:34.862
IT'S GONNA BE WICKED.

09:34.862 --> 09:36.827
SEEING WHAT RICHARD'S VISION
WAS IS AWESOME

09:36.827 --> 09:38.379
BECAUSE AT FIRST,
I DIDN'T SEE IT

09:38.379 --> 09:39.827
WITH
A RIVIERA-Z06 CROSSOVER.

09:39.827 --> 09:41.413
BUT I THINK IT WILL
WORK OUT WELL.

09:41.413 --> 09:43.000
ALL RIGHT.
KICK-ASS.

09:46.862 --> 09:48.137
CHECK IT OUT, RICHARD.

09:48.137 --> 09:49.275
HERE'S YOUR ENGINE
FOR THE RIVIERA.

09:49.275 --> 09:50.586
Richard: SUPER RAD.

09:50.586 --> 09:52.275
WE START WITH AN LT4 ENGINE.

09:52.275 --> 09:55.034
WE SLEEVE THE BLOCK TO BRING
IT UP TO 427 CUBIC INCHES.

09:55.034 --> 09:56.793
IT'S GOT CALLIES CRANK AND RODS,

09:56.793 --> 09:59.344
FORGE PISTONS AND A MAGNUSON
SUPERCHARGER.

09:59.344 --> 10:00.517
-[ WHISTLES ]
-DIG IT.

10:00.517 --> 10:02.000
SO ARE WE GONNA HAVE
STREETABLE,

10:02.000 --> 10:03.448
1,000-ISH HORSEPOWER?

10:03.448 --> 10:05.206
YOU MIGHT EVEN SEE FOUR DIGITS
ON THE SCREEN TODAY.

10:05.206 --> 10:06.551
STOP IT.EXCELLENT.

10:06.551 --> 10:08.275
LET'S FIRE IT UP.
OH, YEAH.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.275
OKAY,
WHERE'S THE THROTTLE?

10:09.275 --> 10:10.931
Man #2:
IT'S THIS ONE ON THE LEFT.

10:10.931 --> 10:12.413
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.

10:12.413 --> 10:14.448
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

10:14.448 --> 10:16.137
-WHOA!
-THERE WE GO!

10:18.689 --> 10:20.482
Richard:
WE'RE AT 3,000 RPMs.

10:20.482 --> 10:21.551
SO YOU'LL BE WATCHING...

10:21.551 --> 10:22.862
RIGHT HERE WILL BE
YOUR POWER NUMBER,

10:22.862 --> 10:24.482
AND THEN THIS
IS YOUR TORQUE NUMBER.

10:24.482 --> 10:25.896
COME ON, BABY.

10:25.896 --> 10:29.034
172...3.

10:29.034 --> 10:31.034
THE GAUGE RIGHT THERE IS
TELLING US HOW MUCH HORSEPOWER

10:31.034 --> 10:34.931
THE MOTOR IS GENERATING
AS IT REACHES ITS MAXIMUM RPM.

10:34.931 --> 10:36.758
[ LAUGHING ]

10:36.758 --> 10:39.551
YEAH!

10:39.551 --> 10:43.620
660...700...
800 HORSEPOWER.

10:43.620 --> 10:45.862
830.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.931
COME ON, BABY.

10:47.931 --> 10:49.275
COME ON.

10:49.275 --> 10:50.827
YEAH.

10:50.827 --> 10:53.689
WE GOT 1,022 FOOT-POUNDS
OF TORQUE

10:53.689 --> 10:55.310
AND ABOUT
984 HORSEPOWER.

10:55.310 --> 10:57.344
BIG DADDY DON GARLITS
MADE A BURNOUT ONE TIME

10:57.344 --> 10:58.655
IN THE QUARTER MILE.

10:58.655 --> 11:00.413
THIS WILL DO IT
FOR, LIKE, 4 MILES.

11:00.413 --> 11:02.482
AND LOOK COOL DOING IT.OH, HELL YEAH.

11:02.482 --> 11:04.000
CAN I REV IT JUST
A LITTLE BIT?

11:04.000 --> 11:05.448
YEAH.

11:05.448 --> 11:06.689
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

11:06.689 --> 11:09.068
-YEAH.
-HA HA!

11:09.068 --> 11:10.655
OKAY, WE BETTER
GET OUT OF HERE

11:10.655 --> 11:12.068
BEFORE WE MAKE HIM
BREAK IT.

11:15.137 --> 11:17.689
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD"...

11:17.689 --> 11:18.965
UGH.
WAS THAT YOUR FINGER?

11:18.965 --> 11:21.000
...THE MONKEYS TAKE THE SWORD
TO A '33 FORD.

11:21.000 --> 11:22.275
EXCALIBUR.

11:22.275 --> 11:23.931
Narrator: AND IS THE 'CUDA
A GRAND THEFT AUTO?

11:23.931 --> 11:25.827
I STOLE THIS CAR
FOR ONLY 45 GRAND.

11:25.827 --> 11:27.344
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY?
-WHAT'S THAT?

11:27.344 --> 11:29.344
"NO REALLY GOOD DEAL
GOES UNPUNISHED."

11:29.344 --> 11:31.413
I THINK IT'S GOOD DEED.

11:35.413 --> 11:37.724
Man #3: I'M NOT GONNA LIE.
I'M AFRAID.

11:40.137 --> 11:42.620
-HEY, THANKS FOR THE HELP.
-YOU GOT IT.

11:42.620 --> 11:43.896
YOU GOT MATER IN THERE
DRIVING.

11:43.896 --> 11:46.724
Mike: WELL, YOU'RE A LITTLE
TO ONE SIDE, MATER.

11:46.724 --> 11:48.206
ACTUALLY, YOU'RE A LOT
TO ONE SIDE.

11:48.206 --> 11:50.000
THIS THING LOOKS LIKE
A RUST BUCKET.

11:50.000 --> 11:52.068
IT'S NOT A RUST BUCKET.
IT'S ACTUALLY REALLY SOLID.

11:52.068 --> 11:54.344
WHAT [BLEEP]
DID YOU PULL THIS OUT OF?

11:54.344 --> 11:57.965
-THIS WAS BASS' TRUCK.
-OH.

11:57.965 --> 11:59.344
THE BABY GATE OVER HERE WORKS.

11:59.344 --> 12:01.689
IT ALREADY CAUGHT TONY.
IT'S ALREADY GOT HIM STUCK.

12:01.689 --> 12:03.655
-ANTIQUE BABY GATE.
-ANTIQUE BABY GATE.

12:03.655 --> 12:05.172
Brian: SO I GOT THIS TRUCK
A COUPLE YEARS AGO,

12:05.172 --> 12:07.413
AND I HAD A VISION FOR IT
IN MY HEAD EVER SINCE I GOT IT,

12:07.413 --> 12:08.896
AND IT MIGHT TAKE THE MONKEYS
A LITTLE WHILE TO COME AROUND

12:08.896 --> 12:10.413
TO MY WAY OF SEEING THINGS,

12:10.413 --> 12:12.655
AND YOU KNOW JEREMY IS ALREADY
COMPLAINING ABOUT THE RUST.

12:12.655 --> 12:14.344
BUT I WANT TO LEAD THEM
THROUGH MY PLAN TO TURN THIS

12:14.344 --> 12:17.241
'33 FORD PICKUP INTO
A TOTALLY BADASS SHOP TRUCK.

12:17.241 --> 12:18.413
LET'S GET TO WORK
BECAUSE WE AIN'T GOT MUCH TIME.

12:18.413 --> 12:20.068
WHAT DO Y'ALL THINK,
TEAR IT UP?

12:20.068 --> 12:21.517
UGH.
WAS THAT YOUR FINGER?

12:21.517 --> 12:22.344
NAH, IT'S FINE.

12:22.344 --> 12:23.689
THAT'S TOO BAD.

12:23.689 --> 12:26.413
AW, MAN.
I BROKE IT.

12:28.413 --> 12:29.551
IT'S LIKE [BLEEP] EXCALIBUR.

12:29.551 --> 12:30.586
RICHARD GAVE US 2 WEEKS

12:30.586 --> 12:32.275
AND 5 GRAND
TO FINISH THIS BUILD,

12:32.275 --> 12:33.827
SO WE CAN'T WASTE
A SINGLE MINUTE.

12:33.827 --> 12:36.068
FIRST, WE'LL STRIP THE '33
DOWN TO THE CHASSIS

12:36.068 --> 12:37.931
SO WE CAN SEND THE FRAME
OUT TO THE SANDBLASTER.

12:37.931 --> 12:40.206
WHEN WE'RE DONE TEARING DOWN
THE '33 FORD,

12:40.206 --> 12:43.137
WE'LL HAVE MIKE PAINT IT
INSTEAD OF SENDING IT TO POWDER.

12:43.137 --> 12:44.758
NOW WE CAN JUST PUT THIS
ON THE GROUND AND STEP ON IT

12:44.758 --> 12:46.275
SO WE CAN STRAIGHTEN IT OUT.

12:46.275 --> 12:47.655
THE ORIGINAL FOUR-CYLINDER
AND DRIVETRAIN WILL GO AWAY

12:47.655 --> 12:51.551
AND BE REPLACED
WITH RICHARD'S FLATHEAD V-8.

12:51.551 --> 12:52.931
OH, YEAH.

12:52.931 --> 12:55.137
I THINK THAT USED TO BE
OLD GAS PRICE SIGN.

12:55.137 --> 12:57.206
YEAH, THAT'S PRETTY FUNNY.

12:57.206 --> 12:58.448
GOOD GOD, MAN.

12:58.448 --> 13:06.103
♪♪

13:06.103 --> 13:09.379
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A FIRE OVER
HERE, PROBABLY NEED SOME WATER.

13:09.379 --> 13:10.689
Mike: NOW, THAT'S STUPID.
LOOK AT THAT.

13:10.689 --> 13:11.965
THAT'S FINE.

13:11.965 --> 13:13.896
LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE
ROASTING MARSHMALLOWS OVER HERE.

13:13.896 --> 13:15.379
GOT THE CAB COMPLETELY
LOOSE NOW,

13:15.379 --> 13:16.758
SO IT CAN GO UP
WHENEVER WE'RE READY.

13:16.758 --> 13:19.275
YEAH, WE CAN POP THE CAB NOW.
HERE WE GO.

13:20.517 --> 13:22.206
WELL, HALLELUJAH.

13:24.379 --> 13:25.586
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

13:25.586 --> 13:28.482
ALL RIGHT.

13:28.482 --> 13:30.827
HELL YEAH, BROTHER.

13:30.827 --> 13:32.068
-MORE RUST.
-OH, COME ON.

13:32.068 --> 13:33.620
YOU REALLY SOLD THEM A PIECE.

13:33.620 --> 13:36.068
THE FRAME ACTUALLY LOOKS
PRETTY DECENT,

13:36.068 --> 13:37.482
IT'S JUST RUSTY.

13:37.482 --> 13:38.655
Brian: NOW, THESE GUYS ARE
REALLY TWITCHY ABOUT RUST,

13:38.655 --> 13:39.517
AND THAT MIGHT BE
BECAUSE RICHARD HAS BROUGHT THEM

13:39.517 --> 13:40.620
SO MANY SURPRISES IN THE PAST,

13:40.620 --> 13:42.000
BUT I KNOW A SOLID TRUCK
WHEN I SEE ONE,

13:42.000 --> 13:44.000
AND THE FRAME UNDER THIS ONE
IS IN EXCELLENT SHAPE.

13:44.000 --> 13:45.827
NOW, SOME MIGHT SEE THE LITTLE
BIT OF RUST AS A PROBLEM,

13:45.827 --> 13:47.827
BUT I SEE THAT AS 85 YEARS
WORTH OF CHARACTER,

13:47.827 --> 13:49.655
AND THAT'S WHY
WE'RE KEEPING THE PATINA.

13:49.655 --> 13:52.551
SO THE MOTOR SHOULD
COME OUT THEN.

13:52.551 --> 13:54.068
-OOH, MOTOR IS DETACHED.
-ALL RIGHT.

13:54.068 --> 13:55.724
THAT'S EVERYTHING
ON THE FRONT, ISN'T IT?

13:55.724 --> 13:57.724
GOOD JOB.
THAT MOTOR MIGHT BE GOOD.

13:57.724 --> 13:59.103
Brian:
PLAYING BY RICHARD'S RULES,

13:59.103 --> 14:00.620
TRYING TO GET THIS TRUCK DONE
AS FAST AS POSSIBLE,

14:00.620 --> 14:02.551
THAT'S, FOR SURE, GONNA BE
A CHALLENGE FOR ME.

14:02.551 --> 14:04.551
ALL RIGHT.
WAITING FOR THE RELEASE.

14:04.551 --> 14:06.689
OH, THERE IT IS.

14:06.689 --> 14:09.586
BUT IT'S HIS TRUCK NOW, AND HE'S
PAYING ME TO APPLY MY VISION.

14:09.586 --> 14:12.275
WELL, THAT'S A SWEET DEAL
FOR ME.

14:12.275 --> 14:13.689
CAN RICHARD MAKE
SOME MONEY ON IT?

14:13.689 --> 14:15.551
WELL, THAT'S UP TO HIM.

14:15.551 --> 14:17.344
BYE, FRAME.

14:17.344 --> 14:19.034
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

14:19.034 --> 14:27.586
♪♪

