-ALL THE WAY AROUND, RIGHT?
-THAT'S COOL.

16:06.620 --> 16:08.620
IT'S GOT A THREE-LENGTH DRAG
REAR END, LIMITED SLIP.

16:08.620 --> 16:10.689
IT'S GOT A TREMEC 5-SPEED,
AIR CONDITIONING.

16:10.689 --> 16:12.103
THAT'S PRETTY RAD ACTUALLY.

16:12.103 --> 16:14.344
NOT NUMBERS-MATCHING,
BUT A LOT OF MODERN UPGRADES,

16:14.344 --> 16:15.827
AND THAT SPELLED PROFIT
IF I COULD GET IT

16:15.827 --> 16:18.172
FOR THE RIGHT PRICE,
SO I TOOK IT FOR A RIDE.

16:22.310 --> 16:23.793
WHOA!

16:23.793 --> 16:25.724
YEAH, IT'S A LITTLE BINDING UP
ON THE TRANNY, TOO.

16:25.724 --> 16:28.000
OKAY, IT HAD SOME MINOR
MECHANICAL ISSUES,

16:28.000 --> 16:29.620
BUT NOTHING MY GUYS CAN'T FIX,

16:29.620 --> 16:31.103
BUT IT HAD PRISTINE
PAINT AND BODY,

16:31.103 --> 16:34.862
WHICH IS THE EXPENSIVE PART,
SO I MADE HIM AN OFFER.

16:34.862 --> 16:36.241
I'D DO $45,000.

16:36.241 --> 16:38.793
YOU GOT CASH MONEY?I ALWAYS HAVE CASH MONEY.

16:40.620 --> 16:41.965
LET'S GO GET YOU
SOME CASH,

16:41.965 --> 16:43.034
AS LONG AS RUSSELL
DIDN'T SPEND IT ALL.

16:43.034 --> 16:45.862
COME ON IN.

16:45.862 --> 16:48.310
SO I STOLE THIS GORGEOUS
'70 'CUDA FOR 45 GRAND,

16:48.310 --> 16:51.896
BUT FOR SOME REASON,
THE MONKEYS ARE WHINING ALREADY.

16:51.896 --> 16:53.379
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING TO SAY?

16:53.379 --> 16:56.068
IT'S GOT A PROBLEM.

16:56.068 --> 16:57.827
YOU'VE GOT TO BE
[BLEEP] KIDDING ME.

16:57.827 --> 16:59.206
YOUR TRANSPORT DRIVER.

16:59.206 --> 17:01.103
SOMEHOW WHEN I HAD THIS CAR
SHIPPED TO TEXAS,

17:01.103 --> 17:02.448
IT GOT CRUNCHED.

17:02.448 --> 17:03.655
IT'S ONE OF THE REASONS
I BOUGHT THE CAR

17:03.655 --> 17:05.310
IS PAINT
AND BODY IS SO EXPENSIVE.

17:05.310 --> 17:08.275
NOW IT'S GONNA COST ME TO FIX
IT, WHICH MEANS LESS PROFIT.

17:08.275 --> 17:09.482
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, THAT'S GREAT.

17:09.482 --> 17:11.655
I BOUGHT A CAR
THAT WAS MECHANICALLY EH

17:11.655 --> 17:14.068
BECAUSE IT WAS PERFECT INTERIOR
AND PAINT AND BODY,

17:14.068 --> 17:15.620
SO LET'S GET IT INTO PAINT
AND BODY FIRST

17:15.620 --> 17:17.862
BECAUSE WE'RE BUSY OVER THERE
AND THEN GET IT OVER TO YOU.

17:17.862 --> 17:19.241
OKAY. AND JUST START
AT THE VERY FRONT.

17:19.241 --> 17:20.862
GO ALL THE WAY TO THE BACK,
EVERY SINGLE THING,

17:20.862 --> 17:22.172
JUST CHECK IT.

17:22.172 --> 17:23.413
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY?
-WHAT'S THAT?

17:23.413 --> 17:25.551
"NO REALLY GOOD DEAL
GOES UNPUNISHED."

17:25.551 --> 17:26.931
I THINK IT'S GOOD DEED.

17:26.931 --> 17:28.068
GOOD [BLEEP] DEAL.

17:28.068 --> 17:30.448
IT'S GOOD DEED.

17:30.448 --> 17:32.517
THAT THING
DOES SOUND BAD.

17:36.241 --> 17:37.551
Jason: YOU KNOW
WHAT'S FUNNY ABOUT THIS

17:37.551 --> 17:40.379
IS RICHARD ALWAYS WANTS
TO BUILD A SHOP TRUCK,

17:40.379 --> 17:42.413
BUT WE'VE BUILT, LIKE,
THREE SHOP TRUCKS,

17:42.413 --> 17:44.000
AND IF YOU NOTICE,
NONE OF THEM ARE STILL HERE.

17:44.000 --> 17:45.172
-YEAH, I'M LOOKING...
-BECAUSE HE SELLS THEM

17:45.172 --> 17:46.275
BEFORE WE CAN EVEN GET
A CHANCE TO USE THEM.

17:46.275 --> 17:47.724
YOU GUYS ARE SAYING THAT.

17:47.724 --> 17:48.586
I'M LOOKING AROUND,
"WHERE IS THE SHOP TRUCK?"

17:48.586 --> 17:49.827
YEAH, EXACTLY.

17:49.827 --> 17:51.241
Brian: IT'S ONLY DAY 2
OF THE '33 MODEL B BUILD,

17:51.241 --> 17:52.275
BUT WE'RE WELL UNDER WAY.

17:52.275 --> 17:53.448
WE GOT THE TRUCK
BLOWN APART YESTERDAY,

17:53.448 --> 17:54.793
AND WHILE THE FRAME
IS AT THE SANDBLASTER,

17:54.793 --> 17:56.206
I'M GOING TO GET TOGETHER
WITH JEREMY

17:56.206 --> 17:57.620
TO FIGURE OUT WHAT TO DO
ABOUT THE PIECE OF FENDER

17:57.620 --> 18:00.551
MISSING FROM THE RIGHT REAR.

18:00.551 --> 18:02.586
THAT FENDER WILL BE THE BEST
PLACE TO START, IN MY OPINION,

18:02.586 --> 18:04.103
BECAUSE
IT'S THE WORST ONE.

18:04.103 --> 18:06.172
IS THIS IS A "STICK IT BACK
TOGETHER AS CLOSE AS IT CAN BE

18:06.172 --> 18:07.931
AND PUT A BIG OLD FAT
MIG-WELD ON IT?"

18:07.931 --> 18:08.965
-NO.
-NO.

18:08.965 --> 18:10.068
I THINK WE SHOULD DO IT...

18:10.068 --> 18:11.620
TREAT IT LIKE WE'RE DOING
ANYTHING ELSE

18:11.620 --> 18:12.724
IN CASE
SOMEWHERE DOWN THE LINE,

18:12.724 --> 18:13.827
SOMEONE WANTS
TO MAKE THIS THING

18:13.827 --> 18:15.931
INTO A NICELY PAINTED,
FINISHED TRUCK.

18:15.931 --> 18:17.103
YEAH.

18:17.103 --> 18:18.344
THEN AT LEAST GIVE THEM
A HEAD START.

18:18.344 --> 18:19.896
WITH ONLY 2 WEEKS TO FINISH
THE BUILD,

18:19.896 --> 18:21.413
IT'S ALL TOO EASY TO DO THINGS
THE QUICK AND DIRTY WAY,

18:21.413 --> 18:22.862
BUT THAT'S NOT MY STYLE.

18:22.862 --> 18:24.517
I'VE NEVER DONE THAT WORKING
BY MYSELF,

18:24.517 --> 18:26.965
AND I'M NOT GOING TO LET THE GAS
MONKEY'S SCHEDULE CHANGE THAT.

18:26.965 --> 18:29.103
I MEAN, WE'RE NOT GONNA GO
CRAZY WITH THE METALWORK,

18:29.103 --> 18:31.137
BUT THERE ARE A FEW THINGS
WE NEED TO FIX JUST FOR...

18:31.137 --> 18:32.655
YOU KNOW, TO MAKE IT USABLE.

18:32.655 --> 18:35.586
ANYTHING WE'RE DOING NEEDS
TO BE DONE RIGHT.

18:35.586 --> 18:38.172
EVEN THOUGH THIS IS A CRUSTY,
OLD, BEAT-UP TRUCK,

18:38.172 --> 18:39.448
I DON'T WANT PEOPLE
TO LOOK AT IT AND SAY,

18:39.448 --> 18:41.689
"OH, THEY DID
TERRIBLE WORK."

18:41.689 --> 18:43.206
RICHARD, HE SEEMS TO THINK
IT'S FAST AND EASY

18:43.206 --> 18:45.172
JUST TO GRAFT A PIECE
ONTO THE EXISTING FENDER.

18:45.172 --> 18:47.068
NOW, I PICKED UP A REPOP
WHEN IT WAS STILL MY PROJECT,

18:47.068 --> 18:48.931
BUT THERE'S STILL THE QUESTION
OF MATCHING THE PATINA.

18:48.931 --> 18:50.551
LET ME GO GET MIKE AND SEE
WHAT HE THINKS ABOUT THIS.

18:50.551 --> 18:51.862
Jeremy: ALL RIGHT.
WELL, SHOOT.

18:51.862 --> 18:52.931
MAKING THE RIGHT DECISION
IS GONNA HAVE

18:52.931 --> 18:54.172
TO INCLUDE
THE PAINT DEPARTMENT.

18:54.172 --> 18:55.965
ALL RIGHT.
I FOUND THE NEW FENDER.

18:55.965 --> 18:58.965
YOU BROUGHT MIKE
WITH YOU.

18:58.965 --> 19:01.482
OUR QUESTION FOR YOU,
MIKE, IS,

19:01.482 --> 19:04.965
WHAT IS FASTER AND BETTER
FOR THIS PARTICULAR JOB?

19:04.965 --> 19:06.448
RICHARD TALKED ABOUT
GRAFTING THE FENDER

19:06.448 --> 19:08.965
AND KEEPING THE PATINA,
BUT HONESTLY,

19:08.965 --> 19:10.793
I THINK IF YOU CAN MATCH
THIS PATINA

19:10.793 --> 19:12.344
TO MAKE IT LOOK
LIKE THE OTHER FENDER

19:12.344 --> 19:14.620
AND KIND OF WHAT'S LEFT HERE,
THAT WOULD BE WAY FASTER.

19:14.620 --> 19:17.586
IF YOU WANT ME TO DO A PATINA
MATCH ON THAT, I CAN DO THAT.

19:17.586 --> 19:18.896
LET'S DO THE WHOLE FENDER.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.241
I'LL HAVE TO FIND
ALL OF THOSE COLORS.

19:20.241 --> 19:21.689
YEAH.
THERE'S ABOUT 50 COLORS

19:21.689 --> 19:23.344
IN, LIKE,
1 SQUARE-INCH HERE, SO...

19:23.344 --> 19:24.896
I THINK GOING WITH A WHOLE
NEW FENDER IS THE RIGHT CALL.

19:24.896 --> 19:26.586
THIS WAY I CAN HAVE JEREMY
MOVE ON TO OTHER WORK

19:26.586 --> 19:29.586
WHILE MIKE MATCHES THE PATINA.

19:29.586 --> 19:30.724
I GOT THIS FOR YOU.

19:30.724 --> 19:33.000
ALL RIGHT.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.827
Mike:
WELL, DO ME A FAVOR.

19:34.827 --> 19:36.862
TAKE THAT FENDER OFF,
AND LET ME HAVE THAT FENDER.

19:36.862 --> 19:39.655
DEAL.

19:39.655 --> 19:41.310
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD"...

19:41.310 --> 19:42.724
THERE IS
A SERIOUS VIBRATION.

19:42.724 --> 19:44.241
...IT'S A 'CUDA CALAMITY...

19:44.241 --> 19:45.448
DAMN, THIS THING
SOUNDS HORRIBLE.

19:45.448 --> 19:47.068
OH, YEAH.

19:47.068 --> 19:51.034
...AS THE MONKEYS TAKE THEIR
FRUSTRATION OUT ON THE '33 FORD.

19:51.034 --> 19:53.103
I DON'T REMEMBER TELLING YOU
IT WAS OKAY TO TEAR IT UP.

19:53.103 --> 19:55.103
YES, YOU DID.

20:00.344 --> 20:02.379
-HERE'S THE TAILGATE.
-SO JUMP ON IT?

20:02.379 --> 20:03.655
Brian: THAT'S HOW
I WOULD DO IT.

20:03.655 --> 20:07.344
SO DO IT MORE LIKE A...

20:07.344 --> 20:08.482
NOT LIKE THAT.
NOT LIKE...

20:08.482 --> 20:09.965
MORE LIKE A SKATEBOARD?

20:09.965 --> 20:11.310
NO, NO.
DON'T DROP IN.

20:11.310 --> 20:12.482
STRAIGHT OFF THE...
DON'T DROP IN ON IT?

20:12.482 --> 20:13.793
DON'T DROP IN ON IT.

20:13.793 --> 20:14.827
Brian: THE TAILGATE
ON THE '33 FORD

20:14.827 --> 20:16.137
HAS DEFINITELY
TAKEN SOME LICKS,

20:16.137 --> 20:17.413
SO OLD TONY HAWK HERE
IS GONNA STRAIGHTEN IT OUT

20:17.413 --> 20:19.551
THE OLD-FASHIONED WAY.

20:19.551 --> 20:21.137
GENTLY, TOO.
GENTLY JUMP?

20:21.137 --> 20:22.517
GENTLY JUMP ON IT.

20:22.517 --> 20:24.000
GENTLY PLACE
MY HEAVY ASS ON IT?

20:24.000 --> 20:26.206
GENTLY PLACE
YOUR HEAVY ASS ON IT.

20:26.206 --> 20:27.689
WHEN YOU'RE
STRAIGHTENING OUT METAL

20:27.689 --> 20:29.413
ON AN 85-YEAR-OLD TRUCK,
SOMETIMES YOUR OWN TWO FEET WORK

20:29.413 --> 20:31.551
AS GOOD AS $10,000
WORTH OF HEAVY MACHINERY.

20:31.551 --> 20:34.655
SEE, IT'S LIKE
A TRAMPOLINE OF STEEL.

20:34.655 --> 20:36.241
IT'S ACTUALLY WORKING,
SO YOU SEE THAT, RICHARD?

20:36.241 --> 20:38.586
A LITTLE DOWN-HOME INGENUITY
CAN SAVE YOU SOME BUCKS.

20:38.586 --> 20:40.517
I THINK YOU ACTUALLY ARE
FIXING IT RIGHT NOW.

20:40.517 --> 20:42.000
ALL RIGHT.

20:42.000 --> 20:43.275
JEREMY STILL NEEDS TO WELD UP
A COUPLE OF ROUGH SPOTS

20:43.275 --> 20:44.793
ON THE TAILGATE BEFORE
HANDING IT OFF TO MIKE.

20:44.793 --> 20:46.379
IN THE MEANTIME,
I'M DOING A ONCE-OVER

20:46.379 --> 20:48.655
ON THE '39 TRANSMISSION
I'VE BEEN SAVING FOR THIS TRUCK.

20:48.655 --> 20:50.275
UGH, THAT'S PRETTY GROSS.

20:50.275 --> 20:52.931
YOU WANT SOME OF THIS?
IT'S LIKE THE...

20:52.931 --> 20:54.310
YOU KNOW, WHEN YOUR MOM
WOULD BAKE YOU A CAKE,

20:54.310 --> 20:57.275
AND SHE'D LET YOU
LICK THE SPATULA.

20:57.275 --> 20:59.793
WHOA!
SLINGING SOME GOO YOUR WAY.

20:59.793 --> 21:01.413
SORRY.

21:01.413 --> 21:03.034
IT KIND OF LOOKS LIKE
IT'S A PIECE OF JUNK RIGHT NOW,

21:03.034 --> 21:04.137
BUT IT'S REALLY NOT.

21:04.137 --> 21:05.689
JUST HAVE TO CLEAN UP
THE OUTSIDE,

21:05.689 --> 21:07.655
MAKE SURE EVERYTHING INSIDE
IS AS GOOD AS I THINK IT IS

21:07.655 --> 21:10.172
AND REBUILD IT LATER BEFORE
BOLTING IT INTO THE TRUCK.

21:10.172 --> 21:11.448
HOPEFULLY SOMEONE HID,

21:11.448 --> 21:13.241
LIKE, THOUSANDS
OF DOLLARS INSIDE HERE.

21:13.241 --> 21:15.275
UGH, NO.

21:15.275 --> 21:16.793
SEE, IT LOOKS
PRETTY NICE INSIDE.

21:16.793 --> 21:19.275
IT'S REALLY CLEAN.
I THINK THAT'S GONNA WORK.

21:19.275 --> 21:21.517
LOOK.
"'39 FORD."

21:21.517 --> 21:23.620
IT'S KIND OF, LIKE, THE ORIGINAL
HOT-ROD TRANSMISSION.

21:23.620 --> 21:25.137
EVERYBODY THAT HAD A FLATHEAD
IN THEIR HOT ROD,

21:25.137 --> 21:28.000
THEY WANTED THIS TRANSMISSION
BECAUSE IT HAD A FLOOR SHIFT

21:28.000 --> 21:29.275
AND CAN HOLD UP TO
A LITTLE MORE HORSEPOWER.

21:29.275 --> 21:30.896
IT'S A LITTLE GUY.

21:30.896 --> 21:32.103
IT'S JUST A LITTLE FELLA.

21:32.103 --> 21:33.586
THIS TRANSMISSION
IS IN GOOD SHAPE,

21:33.586 --> 21:34.896
SO I'LL SEND IT OVER TO MIKE
TO PAINT IT ALONG

21:34.896 --> 21:36.448
WITH THE INTERIOR OF THE CAB.

21:36.448 --> 21:37.965
HEY.
VROOM, VROOM.

21:37.965 --> 21:39.172
Tony: THIS THING DOESN'T
STEER VERY WELL.

21:39.172 --> 21:40.655
VROOM, VROOM.

21:40.655 --> 21:41.931
I'M TRYING TO GET IT STARTED,
BUT IT WON'T RUN.

21:41.931 --> 21:43.586
IT SEEMS TO BE RUNNING
JUST FINE.

21:43.586 --> 21:45.241
IT'S ONE OF THEM
ELECTRIC TRUCKS.

21:45.241 --> 21:47.793
-IT'S AN ELECTRIC TRUCK.
-VERY QUIET.

21:47.793 --> 21:53.689
♪♪

21:53.689 --> 21:54.965
-NOT BAD.
-YEAH, IT LOOKS GOOD, MAN.

21:54.965 --> 21:56.068
Tony: NOT BAD FOR A DAY'S WORTH
OF A WORK.

21:56.068 --> 21:57.620
Jason: YEAH, EXACTLY
FOR HOW BAD IT WAS.

21:57.620 --> 21:58.965
-SEE IT NO MORE.
-JUST LIKE NEW.

21:58.965 --> 22:00.551
-HELL YEAH.
-IT'S WHAT THEY DO.

22:00.551 --> 22:02.000
KICK-ASS.

22:02.000 --> 22:02.965
-YEAH, THAT'S RAD.
-AND A DAY'S WORK...

22:02.965 --> 22:03.896
A DAY'S WORTH OF WORK.

22:03.896 --> 22:05.413
YEAH, IT LOOKS GREAT.
PERFECT.

22:05.413 --> 22:10.068
COY AND TONY DID A FANTASTIC JOB
ON THE PAINT AND BODY REPAIR,

22:10.068 --> 22:12.655
BUT THE BIGGER PROBLEM
IS HOW THIS THING DRIVES.

22:12.655 --> 22:15.103
YEAH, IT'S A LITTLE BINDING
UP ON THE TRANNY.

22:15.103 --> 22:18.103
OKAY, SO WHEN I BOUGHT
THIS CAR...

22:18.103 --> 22:19.379
IT DOESN'T SHIFT SUPER WELL.
-YEP.

22:19.379 --> 22:21.448
IT'S GOT A WEIRD NOISE
IN THE REAR END,

22:21.448 --> 22:24.689
AND IT OBVIOUSLY NEEDS TIRES,
SO WE NEED TO GIVE IT

22:24.689 --> 22:26.517
A GOOD ONE-THROUGH
FROM THE FRONT TO THE BACK.

22:26.517 --> 22:28.482
SO MOPARS ARE ALWAYS HOT,
AND A '70 'CUDA

22:28.482 --> 22:29.896
HAS ALWAYS BEEN A POPULAR CAR,

22:29.896 --> 22:31.655
AND PEOPLE WILL SHELL OUT
TOP DOLLAR FOR THEM,

22:31.655 --> 22:33.482
ESPECIALLY ONE
IN THIS CONDITION,

22:33.482 --> 22:35.344
SO I'M GONNA LIST IT
FOR SALE ON THE OLD INTERWEBS.

22:35.344 --> 22:37.241
-GO FOR A RIDE?
-YEAH, LET'S DO IT.

22:37.241 --> 22:38.517
I'M COUNTING ON YOU, JASON.

22:38.517 --> 22:39.758
LET'S DO IT.

22:39.758 --> 22:43.137
Tony:
UH, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

22:43.137 --> 22:45.689
YEAH.
WOW, A LOT OF WOBBLING.

22:47.482 --> 22:48.896
GOLLY, MAN.

22:48.896 --> 22:51.068
FEEL THE...
HEAR THE KNOCK ON THOSE TIRES?

22:51.068 --> 22:53.241
-WHAT IS THAT?
-WE MAY NOT GET VERY FAR.

22:53.241 --> 22:54.620
IS THAT THE DRIVESHAFT?

22:54.620 --> 22:57.448
DUDE, I DON'T KNOW.
THERE IS A SERIOUS VIBRATION.

22:57.448 --> 22:59.344
OH, GOD.

22:59.344 --> 23:00.896
DEFINITELY
AN ISSUE THERE.

23:00.896 --> 23:03.793
TRY TO KEEP IT ON THE PEDAL
AS MOST I CAN.

23:03.793 --> 23:05.482
OOF.

23:05.482 --> 23:10.482
♪♪

23:10.482 --> 23:11.896
AFTER THE TEST-DRIVE,
TONY AND I WERE LEFT

23:11.896 --> 23:13.827
WITH MORE QUESTIONS
THAN ANSWERS.

23:13.827 --> 23:15.275
WE'RE NOT REAL SURE WHAT'S
GOING ON WITH THE REAR END,

23:15.275 --> 23:16.896
BUT WE'VE GOT A LOT
OF NOISE HAPPENING,

23:16.896 --> 23:19.000
AND WHAT'S MORE CONCERNING
IS THAT UNDERNEATH THE CAR,

23:19.000 --> 23:21.206
NOTHING LOOSE, NOTHING
BROKEN THAT WE CAN SEE.

23:21.206 --> 23:22.896
IT'S INTERNALLY INSIDE THE HUB,

23:22.896 --> 23:24.689
SO WE'RE GONNA TAKE
A LOOK IN THERE.

23:24.689 --> 23:26.896
-SHE IS PRETTY.
-SHE'S BRAND-NEW.

23:26.896 --> 23:29.241
IT'S GOT TO BE IN THE PRELOAD
OF THIS THING,

23:29.241 --> 23:31.068
JUST HOPPING A TOOTH
OR SOMETHING.

23:31.068 --> 23:32.517
EVEN AFTER TEARING
THE DIFFERENTIAL APART,

23:32.517 --> 23:34.275
WE DON'T SEE ANYTHING
WORN OR TORN UP.

23:34.275 --> 23:35.931
IN FACT, IT ALL LOOKS BRAND-NEW.

23:35.931 --> 23:37.448
THIS IS GETTING WEIRD.

23:37.448 --> 23:39.517
THE ONLY THING I CAN THINK
IS THOSE GEARS ARE SLOPPING.

23:39.517 --> 23:40.758
THEY'RE MISSING A TOOTH
OR SKIPPING

23:40.758 --> 23:42.000
OR JUST HITTING THEM
REALLY HARD.

23:42.000 --> 23:43.517
IT'S REALLY FRUSTRATING.

23:43.517 --> 23:45.862
EVEN WITH OUR COMBINED YEARS
OF EXPERIENCE, WE GET STUMPED.

23:45.862 --> 23:47.275
THE DRIVESHAFT
IS RUBBING.

23:47.275 --> 23:48.310
WELL, THAT WOULD EXPLAIN
WHY IT SOUNDS LIKE

23:48.310 --> 23:49.551
IT'S HITTING THE FLOOR.

23:49.551 --> 23:51.413
YEAH, YOU CAN SEE
THE RUB MARK THERE.

23:51.413 --> 23:53.448
-OH, YEAH.
-IT'S RUBBING ON THAT HOOP.

23:53.448 --> 23:54.551
YEP.

23:54.551 --> 23:56.172
BOOM.
I THINK I FOUND THE PROBLEM.

23:56.172 --> 23:57.793
THERE'S A HOOP RUBBING
ON THE DRIVESHAFT.

23:57.793 --> 23:59.068
WE'LL YANK THAT SUCKER OFF...

23:59.068 --> 24:01.206
IT HOLDS THE DRIVESHAFT.
STUPID HOOP.

24:01.206 --> 24:02.724
...TAKE IT FOR ANOTHER
TEST DRIVE,

24:02.724 --> 24:05.034
AND THIS MYSTERY
SHOULD BE SOLVED.

24:05.034 --> 24:06.758
SIMPLE.

24:09.413 --> 24:10.620
MAN, THIS THING
SOUNDS HORRIBLE.

24:10.620 --> 24:13.000
OH, YEAH.

24:13.000 --> 24:14.551
OH, MY GOD.

24:14.551 --> 24:16.896
WOW.
I GIVE.

24:16.896 --> 24:18.517
THE GREEN MONSTER
WINS THIS BATTLE.

24:18.517 --> 24:20.413
I THINK I HEAR MIKE
CALLING ME FOR HELP.

24:20.413 --> 24:21.310
GOT TO GO.

24:21.310 --> 24:22.551
MAN, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

24:22.551 --> 24:25.068
THIS HAS GOT SOME TERRIBLE NOISE
COMING FROM THE REAR.

24:25.068 --> 24:26.241
-HUH.
-ALMOST LIKE THE REAR END

24:26.241 --> 24:27.965
IS GONNA COME APART
INSIDE THE CAR.

24:27.965 --> 24:30.068
RICHARD IS ON ME TO GET THIS
'CUDA DONE, BUT I'M STUMPED.

24:30.068 --> 24:32.379
IF JEREMY HAS ANY IDEAS,
I'M ALL EARS.

24:32.379 --> 24:35.896
CHECK OUT THIS.

24:35.896 --> 24:37.241
OH.

24:37.241 --> 24:38.517
IT LOOKS FINE, LIKE,
IF YOU DON'T KNOW.

24:38.517 --> 24:39.620
BUT, YEAH, BUT I KNOW
TO LOOK THERE.

24:39.620 --> 24:41.965
-BUT LOOK AT THE OTHER SIDE.
-YEAH.

24:41.965 --> 24:43.517
THESE BRACKETS
ARE ALWAYS STRAIGHT.

24:43.517 --> 24:45.137
THEY'RE NEVER LIKE THAT.
-OVER HALF AN INCH?

24:45.137 --> 24:46.482
OH, IT'S OVER PRETTY GOOD.

24:46.482 --> 24:48.172
RIGHT AWAY, WHENEVER I LOOK BACK
AT THE READ END,

24:48.172 --> 24:50.000
I CAN SEE THAT ONE
OF THE 4-LINK TABS

24:50.000 --> 24:51.620
IS COMPLETELY BENT.

24:51.620 --> 24:53.551
SO APPARENTLY AT SOME POINT,
IT'S BEEN OVERLOADED,

24:53.551 --> 24:56.551
AND THAT PROBABLY EXPLAINS
WHY THE DRIVESHAFT WAS RUBBING.

24:56.551 --> 24:57.931
SO UNDER PRESSURE,
IT'S TORQUING.

24:57.931 --> 24:59.551
YEAH, SO THAT'S
THE TRACK BAR.

24:59.551 --> 25:00.931
THAT'S WHAT KEEPS THE READ
END UNDER THE CAR STRAIGHT.

25:00.931 --> 25:02.413
MM-HMM.

25:02.413 --> 25:04.793
AND WITH THAT BEING BENT,
THE REAR END IS THAT WAY.

25:04.793 --> 25:05.965
WHICH WAY DID YOU SAY
IT WAS RUBBING?

25:05.965 --> 25:07.103
-YEP.
-IT WAS RUBBING DRIVER SIDE?

25:07.103 --> 25:08.413
YEAH, MM-HMM, YEAH.

25:08.413 --> 25:10.172
WELL, EVERYTHING SHOULD BE
PUSHED THAT WAY

25:10.172 --> 25:11.689
BY THE BEND
BEING THIS WAY.

25:11.689 --> 25:13.172
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO
PULL ALL THIS DOWN.

25:13.172 --> 25:14.344
YEAH.

25:14.344 --> 25:15.448
WE'LL STRAIGHTEN
THESE TWO TABS UP

25:15.448 --> 25:16.655
AND GET THEM NICE
AND STRAIGHT

25:16.655 --> 25:17.551
AND THEN RUN A GUSSET
DOWN THE FRONT OF IT.

25:17.551 --> 25:19.068
JUST BOX THEM IN.

25:19.068 --> 25:20.655
RICHARD TOLD JASON HE NEEDS
THE CAR BACK REALLY QUICK,

25:20.655 --> 25:22.724
BUT WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO HOLD
HIM UP AT LEAST ANOTHER DAY.

25:22.724 --> 25:25.000
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO TAKE
THIS APART, STRAIGHTEN IT.

25:25.000 --> 25:28.034
THAT WILL BE THE FUN PART,
CLEAN IT UP, WELD IN A GUSSET,

25:28.034 --> 25:30.034
AND THEN REPAINT IT
AND REASSEMBLE IT.

25:30.034 --> 25:31.793
THAT'S PRETTY MUCH
A DAY'S SETBACK.

25:31.793 --> 25:33.482
YEAH.

25:33.482 --> 25:39.448
♪♪

25:39.448 --> 25:43.000
Mike: SO THEY WANT ME
TO MATCH PATINA.

25:43.000 --> 25:46.310
MAKES PERFECT SENSE.
HAVE FUN WITH THAT ONE.

25:46.310 --> 25:48.620
IT'S PROBABLY THE EASIEST
PAINT JOB EVER.

25:48.620 --> 25:52.896
WE'RE PUTTING A NEW FENDER
ON THE '33 FORD PICKUP.

25:52.896 --> 25:54.068
BOOM.

25:54.068 --> 25:55.724
MIKE, WE GOT
A FENDER FOR YOU.

25:55.724 --> 25:57.517
BRIAN MADE THE CALL
TO JUST SPEND RICHARD'S MONEY

25:57.517 --> 26:01.137
AND REPLACE IT RATHER THAN GO
TO TOWN WELDING ON IT.

26:01.137 --> 26:02.724
SO NOW I HAVE TO WORK
SOME REAL MAGIC,

26:02.724 --> 26:05.896
CREATING A FAUX PATINA
TO MATCH THE REST OF THE TRUCK.

26:05.896 --> 26:08.379
I MEAN, IT'S EASY,
BUT IT'S NOT EASY.

26:08.379 --> 26:10.241
THE CHALLENGE IS MATCHING
THE SAME LAYERS OF PAINT

26:10.241 --> 26:12.620
THAT HAVE BEEN ON THE TRUCK
FOR MORE THAN 80 YEARS.

26:12.620 --> 26:15.724
DARK GREEN BECAUSE
THAT'S OBVIOUSLY THE BASE ONE.

26:15.724 --> 26:18.724
THEN SOMEBODY REPAINTED IT
AND THEN REPAINTED IT AGAIN,

26:18.724 --> 26:21.586
SO THAT'S THE PLAN.

26:21.586 --> 26:23.103
FIRST, I'M GONNA SANDBLAST

26:23.103 --> 26:24.965
THE BLACK ELECTROCOAT
OFF THE NEW FENDER.

26:24.965 --> 26:26.344
IT'S THERE TO PREVENT RUST,

26:26.344 --> 26:28.275
BUT IT WILL BE MORE
AUTHENTIC WITHOUT IT.

26:28.275 --> 26:32.586
ANYWAY, A LITTLE RUST WILL WORK
IN MY FAVOR DOWN THE ROAD.

26:32.586 --> 26:34.965
MOST JOBS NEED A LOT OF
TENDER LOVE AND CARE.

26:34.965 --> 26:37.517
THIS ONE CALLS FOR A LOT
OF DINGS AND SCRATCHES.

26:37.517 --> 26:38.758
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

26:38.758 --> 26:39.931
TRYING TO MAKE IT LOOK
LIKE THE REST OF IT.

26:39.931 --> 26:42.137
GOT TO HAVE
SOME DENTS IN IT.

26:42.137 --> 26:44.068
[ SIGHS ]

26:47.206 --> 26:49.517
THE HARDEST PART IS PROBABLY
GETTING THE COLORS RIGHT.

26:49.517 --> 26:52.965
THE TRICK IS HOW THEY GET
LAYERED ON THE FENDER.

26:52.965 --> 26:55.517
FEEL FREE TO TRY
THIS ONE AT HOME, KIDS.

26:55.517 --> 26:56.827
IN BETWEEN BASE COATS,

26:56.827 --> 26:58.448
I'M DABBING
ON SOME BUFFING COMPOUND.

26:58.448 --> 27:01.344
WHEREVER I SMEAR THAT STUFF ON,
THE PAINT WON'T STICK.

27:04.103 --> 27:07.137
I WANT THE TEXTURE
THAT THAT'S GOT,

27:07.137 --> 27:09.482
SO ONCE I'M DONE SHOOTING
MY BASE COATS,

27:09.482 --> 27:11.620
I'LL JUST WIPE ALL THIS OFF,

27:11.620 --> 27:13.793
AND THERE WILL BE DIFFERENT
LAYERS OF PAINT.

27:13.793 --> 27:15.517
OR AT LEAST THAT'S THE PLAN.

27:18.172 --> 27:20.103
AND WHEN IT GETS WIPED OFF,
IT STARTS LOOKING LIKE

27:20.103 --> 27:22.827
80 YEARS OF WEAR AND TEAR.

27:22.827 --> 27:24.827
A LITTLE MORE RANDOMIZED TLC.

27:27.965 --> 27:29.551
AND AFTER JUST A COUPLE HOURS
OF WORK,

27:29.551 --> 27:32.413
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO TELL MY
FAUX PATINA FROM THE REAL DEAL.

27:32.413 --> 27:34.620
-LOOKS GOOD TO ME.
-I THINK IT'D FIT RIGHT IN.

27:34.620 --> 27:35.862
Brian: DAMN,
IT LOOKS PRETTY CLOSE.

27:35.862 --> 27:37.827
I THINK WE CAN LIVE
WITH THAT, DEFINITELY.

27:37.827 --> 27:40.965
COME ON, DUDE.

27:40.965 --> 27:43.310
YOU CAN'T EVER TELL HIM
THAT HE CAN TEAR SOMETHING UP.

27:43.310 --> 27:45.344
I DON'T REMEMBER TELLING HIM
IT WAS OKAY TO TEAR IT UP.

27:45.344 --> 27:48.517
YES, YOU DID.

27:48.517 --> 27:51.206
LOOK AT THAT.

27:51.206 --> 27:53.034
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD,"

27:53.034 --> 27:55.241
THE MONKEYS POUNCE
ON THE '33 FORD...

27:55.241 --> 27:56.724
-ALMOST.
-IT DEFINITELY MOVED.

27:56.724 --> 27:58.275
Jeremy: THIS IS HOW ALL
THE BEST SHOPS DO IT.

27:58.275 --> 28:00.517
I THINK THE CAR
IS WORTH 75 GRAND.

28:00.517 --> 28:02.655
Narrator: ...AS RICHARD'S
'CUDA CATCHES A SNAG.

28:02.655 --> 28:04.620
$50,000.
DADGUM, DUDE.

28:04.620 --> 28:06.689
GIVE ME A BREAK.

28:06.689 --> 28:08.275
IT'S GREEN.

28:12.862 --> 28:14.896
WAIT UP.
I'M EATING A BANANA.

28:14.896 --> 28:15.931
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

28:15.931 --> 28:17.827
DID YOU JUST SAY,
"ABOUT TIME?"

28:17.827 --> 28:19.413
-YEAH.
-BANANA.

28:19.413 --> 28:22.827
WHOO!

28:22.827 --> 28:25.172
WE'RE JUST A FEW DAYS
INTO THE '33 FORD BUILD.

28:25.172 --> 28:26.896
WE'RE KEEPING THE PATINA,
BUT MIKE GOT A JUMP START

28:26.896 --> 28:29.103
ON PAINTING THE INTERIOR
AND SANDBLASTING THE FIREWALL.

28:29.103 --> 28:31.448
WHEN YOU SANDBLASTED THIS,
DID YOU THINK ABOUT THE FACT

28:31.448 --> 28:33.586
THAT IT'S BACKWARDS BACK HERE?

28:33.586 --> 28:35.034
-YEAH, I DIDN'T CARE.
-YOU DIDN'T CARE.

28:35.034 --> 28:37.241
FAIR ENOUGH.
-WE'RE GETTING NEW GLASS ANYWAY.

28:37.241 --> 28:38.862
I LIKE THE TAN COLOR.
HOW WE DOING ON TIME?

28:38.862 --> 28:41.620
WE'RE ONLY 2 1/2 DAYS IN
RIGHT NOW BY MY CLOCK.

28:41.620 --> 28:43.931
SO WHAT I'M ABOUT TO TELL YOU
IS A SECRET.

28:43.931 --> 28:45.275
I MEAN, THIS MIGHT BE A NEW
PRODUCTIVITY RECORD

28:45.275 --> 28:46.965
FOR THE MONKEYS,
AND I CAN'T TELL THEM THAT

28:46.965 --> 28:48.793
BECAUSE THEN THEY MIGHT DREAM UP
A WHOLE BUNCH OF EXTRA [BLEEP]

28:48.793 --> 28:51.862
TO DO AND BLOW THEIR LEAD
ON THIS TRUCK, SO ZIP IT.

28:51.862 --> 28:53.379
WHAT COLOR WE PAINTING
THE FRAME?

28:53.379 --> 28:56.310
SAME AS THE BODY, THAT KIND OF
OF FADED-GREEN-LOOKING COLOR.

28:56.310 --> 28:57.413
AND WHAT'S THE DEAL WITH THE BED

28:57.413 --> 28:58.724
BECAUSE I SAW
IT HAS A RIP IN IT?

28:58.724 --> 29:01.482
THE BED FLOOR IS...
IT'S KIND OF TRASHED.

29:01.482 --> 29:03.172
WE WANT TO WELD IT UP.

29:03.172 --> 29:04.379
-WE'RE GONNA FIX THAT.
-YEAH, WE'RE GONNA WELD IT UP,

29:04.379 --> 29:05.827
AND WE'RE GOING
TO MATTE CLEAR IT.

29:05.827 --> 29:08.103
WE'RE GONNA LEAVE
ALL THE REST OF IT OLD.

29:08.103 --> 29:09.551
SOME KIND OF COATING
SO THAT WHATEVER HE PUTS

29:09.551 --> 29:10.931
ON THE BACK ON HERE
DOESN'T TRANSFER THE RUST

29:10.931 --> 29:12.310
TO WHATEVER IT IS
YOU'RE PUTTING IN HERE.

29:12.310 --> 29:13.862
Richard:
WHAT'S THAT HOLE FOR?

29:13.862 --> 29:15.137
YOU PUT A PENNY DOWN THERE,
AND IT STARTS THE TRUCK UP.

29:15.137 --> 29:16.241
THIS IS TRICKY

29:16.241 --> 29:17.931
BECAUSE IF WE PUT
TOO MUCH INTO THIS BUILD

29:17.931 --> 29:19.862
AND MAKE IT TOO COOL,
THE COST GOES UP,

29:19.862 --> 29:21.931
AND THE NUMBER OF BUYERS
THAT MIGHT WANT IT GOES DOWN,

29:21.931 --> 29:23.862
AND I NEED BUYERS.

29:23.862 --> 29:25.068
ALL RIGHT. Y'ALL LOOK LIKE
Y'ALL ARE DOING GOOD.

29:25.068 --> 29:26.137
I'M GONNA GO FIND SOMETHING
TO DO UP FRONT.

29:26.137 --> 29:27.413
WAIT, IS HE ACTUALLY HAPPY
ABOUT THIS?

29:27.413 --> 29:28.517
I THINK
THAT WAS A COMPLIMENT.

29:28.517 --> 29:29.758
I WISH I WOULD
HAVE RECORDED THAT.

29:29.758 --> 29:31.310
BUT I'M NOT GONNA GO
WITH THAT.

29:31.310 --> 29:32.758
LET'S JUST KEEP ROLLING
BECAUSE TOMORROW IT WILL CHANGE.

29:32.758 --> 29:34.689
YOU GONNA GO PAINT
THE FRAME?

29:34.689 --> 29:43.724
♪♪

29:43.724 --> 29:46.655
WELL, JUST LIKE WE TALKED
ON THE PHONE, HERE SHE IS.

29:46.655 --> 29:49.068
AND SHE'S
A REAL V-CODE 'CUDA?

29:49.068 --> 29:50.482
YEP.
ALL RIGHT.

29:50.482 --> 29:51.862
SURE IS.

29:51.862 --> 29:53.655
I GOT THIS CAR DOWN IN FLORIDA
JUST A WHILE BACK,

29:53.655 --> 29:55.620
AND THE PEOPLE
THAT DID IT DIDN'T QUITE KNOW

29:55.620 --> 29:57.379
WHAT THEY WERE DOING,
AND WE BROUGHT IT BACK,

29:57.379 --> 30:00.068
BUT IT'S A 4-LINK,
COILOVERS FRONT AND BACK,

30:00.068 --> 30:01.620
FOUR-WHEEL DISC BRAKES,

30:01.620 --> 30:04.310
SO IT'S ALL SET UP LIKE
WHAT ONE WOULD CALL A RESTOMOD,

30:04.310 --> 30:06.275
BUT, YOU KNOW, IT'S STILL
READY TO ROCK 'N' ROLL.

30:06.275 --> 30:07.482
COOL.

30:07.482 --> 30:08.551
I ALWAYS FORGET WHERE
THESE THINGS ARE.

30:08.551 --> 30:10.275
MY NAME IS BOBBY HOEY,

30:10.275 --> 30:12.379
AND I'M FROM LAFAYETTE,
LOUISIANA.

30:12.379 --> 30:14.034
THEY'RE RIGHT UP IN HERE
SOMEWHERE.

30:14.034 --> 30:16.517
I'M ALWAYS LOOKING FOR 'CUDAS
BECAUSE MOPAR MUSCLE

30:16.517 --> 30:19.344
ALWAYS BRINGS A LOT OF MONEY,
AND SO ANY TIME I SEE ONE,

30:19.344 --> 30:21.413
I ALWAYS TRY TO GO
AND TAKE A LOOK AT IT,

30:21.413 --> 30:23.689
SEE IF I CAN MAYBE
MAKE SOME MONEY WITH IT.

30:25.517 --> 30:26.655
Richard: SO LIKE I SAID,

30:26.655 --> 30:27.827
IT JUST WASN'T EXECUTED
REAL WELL,

30:27.827 --> 30:30.241
BUT IT IS A REAL 440
SIX-PACK CAR,

30:30.241 --> 30:32.586
BUT IT IS NOT NUMBERS-MATCHING
AS FAR AS THE MOTOR GOES.

30:32.586 --> 30:35.172
EVERYTHING ON THE CAR
IS SOLID, SUPER NICE.

30:35.172 --> 30:37.586
YEAH, IT'S JUST AS NICE
UNDERNEATH AS IT IS ON TOP.

30:37.586 --> 30:39.689
IT'S A REALLY
BEAUTIFUL CAR.

30:39.689 --> 30:41.448
AND THAT'S YOUR FAVORITE COLOR,
I BELIEVE.

30:41.448 --> 30:42.862
FOR SURE.

30:42.862 --> 30:44.586
BOB'S GOT THAT LOUISIANA DRAWL,
IF YOU WILL,

30:44.586 --> 30:47.275
YOU KNOW, KIND OF SLOW,
BUT HE KNOWS HIS MOPARS,

30:47.275 --> 30:49.862
AND HE DOESN'T WANT TO BE
BAMBOOZLED BY THIS CITY SLICKER.

30:49.862 --> 30:51.862
Bobby: WHAT I'VE SEEN
IS THE RIGHT COLOR,

30:51.862 --> 30:54.379
THE SASSY GREEN LIKE
THEY LIKE TO CALL IT.

30:54.379 --> 30:56.827
IT'S REAL POPULAR, AND IT'S GOT
A LOT OF OPTIONS IN IT

30:56.827 --> 30:58.482
THAT'S REALLY GONNA HELP
MAKE IT SELL

30:58.482 --> 31:00.172
IF I CAN GET IT BOUGHT TODAY.

31:00.172 --> 31:02.000
WHAT KIND OF MONEY
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

31:02.000 --> 31:03.034
WELL, LET'S TAKE A RIDE.

31:03.034 --> 31:04.275
THEN WE CAN TALK MONEY.
OKAY.

31:04.275 --> 31:05.724
LET ME SHOW YOU
WHAT IT WILL DO.

31:05.724 --> 31:15.655
♪♪

31:15.655 --> 31:18.379
♪♪

31:18.379 --> 31:20.137
PRETTY SOLID LITTLE CAR.

31:20.137 --> 31:21.827
-EVERYTHING UNDER IT'S NEW.
-YEAH.

31:21.827 --> 31:24.344
MAN, IF YOU HAD THIS CAR
IN 1970, YOU WERE A BAD DUDE.

31:24.344 --> 31:25.862
OH, YEAH, FOR SURE.

31:25.862 --> 31:29.448
IF YOU HAD THIS CAR IN 1975,
YOU WAS STILL A BAD DUDE.

31:29.448 --> 31:31.827
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

31:31.827 --> 31:32.620
WHAT DO YOU PLAN ON DOING
WITH A CAR

31:32.620 --> 31:33.724
LIKE THIS IF YOU GET IT?

31:33.724 --> 31:35.344
GONNA DRIVE IT,
PROBABLY A LITTLE BIT,

31:35.344 --> 31:36.931
ENJOY IT, AND THEN...

31:36.931 --> 31:38.206
SEND HER ON
DOWN THE ROAD?

31:38.206 --> 31:40.068
-YES, SIR.
-THAT'S WHAT I USED TO DO

31:40.068 --> 31:41.482
BEFORE I STARTED DOING THIS
FOR A LIVING.

31:41.482 --> 31:42.655
YOU KNOW WHAT?

31:42.655 --> 31:44.172
AT THE END OF THE DAY,
IT'S A JOB.

31:44.172 --> 31:45.413
GOT TO SELL THEM.

31:45.413 --> 31:47.172
THAT'S RIGHT.

31:47.172 --> 31:48.482
Richard: SELLING IS
WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT,

31:48.482 --> 31:50.586
AND EVEN THOUGH HE MAY
NOT SOUND ENTHUSIASTIC,

31:50.586 --> 31:52.931
I'M PRETTY SURE LOUISIANA
BOB IS HOOKED ON THIS 'CUDA.

31:52.931 --> 31:55.724
NOW ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS REEL HIM IN.

31:55.724 --> 31:57.827
IT'S A BADASS LITTLE RIDE.

31:57.827 --> 32:00.000
Bobby: WHAT I THINK STANDS OUT
MOST ABOUT THE CAR IS

32:00.000 --> 32:01.758
IT'S VERY
HIGHLY DETAILED.

32:01.758 --> 32:03.241
IT'S GOT THE RIGHT OPTIONS.

32:03.241 --> 32:05.482
IT'S GOT THE SHAKER HOOD ON IT,
WHICH IS ALL PLUSES,

32:05.482 --> 32:07.482
AND IT'S JUST
A GORGEOUS-LOOKING CAR,

32:07.482 --> 32:09.655
SO I HOPE
I CAN GET IT BOUGHT TODAY.

32:09.655 --> 32:11.206
Richard:
I PAID $45,000 FOR THE 'CUDA,

32:11.206 --> 32:13.206
BUT WITH A DAY OF BODYWORK
AND ALL THE PARTS AND TIME

32:13.206 --> 32:14.620
THAT IT TOOK TO FIX
THE BACK FENDER,

32:14.620 --> 32:17.103
I'M GONNA NEED AT LEAST
$47,000 TO BREAK EVEN.

32:17.103 --> 32:19.620
I THINK THE CAR
IS WORTH 75 GRAND.

32:19.620 --> 32:21.793
I CAN PROBABLY DO A LITTLE
BETTER THAN THAT, YOU KNOW,

32:21.793 --> 32:24.275
SO I'D PROBABLY SAY
SOMEWHERE IN THE HIGH 60s

32:24.275 --> 32:25.275
TO GET IT BOUGHT.

32:25.275 --> 32:28.482
I WAS THINKING
MORE 40-ISH.

32:28.482 --> 32:30.448
YOU CAN'T EVEN BUY A BEAT-UP
ONE OF THESE FOR $40,000

32:30.448 --> 32:31.620
SITTING
IN SOMEBODY'S GARAGE.

32:31.620 --> 32:32.586
HOW ABOUT 60 GRAND?

32:32.586 --> 32:33.862
I MEAN,
I KNOW WHAT I GOT IN IT,

32:33.862 --> 32:36.241
SO AS LONG AS I CAN
BREAK OUT OF IT.

32:36.241 --> 32:38.103
RIGHT THEN AND THERE,
I KNEW THAT I COULD PROBABLY

32:38.103 --> 32:40.655
GET IT BOUGHT FOR WHAT I WAS
HOPING TO GET IT BOUGHT

32:40.655 --> 32:43.482
BECAUSE HE ALWAYS
TENDS TO SHOOT HIGH.

32:43.482 --> 32:45.448
$50,000.
DADGUM, DUDE.

32:45.448 --> 32:46.758
GIVE ME A BREAK.

32:46.758 --> 32:47.965
MAN, YOU'RE
FROM LOUISIANA.

32:47.965 --> 32:49.137
-IT'S GREEN.
-THAT'S OIL MONEY.

32:49.137 --> 32:50.551
WE DON'T LIKE GREEN
IN LOUISIANA.

32:50.551 --> 32:51.793
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

32:51.793 --> 32:53.517
I MIGHT BRING IT BACK
AND PAINT IT PURPLE.

32:53.517 --> 32:54.931
YOU'RE HERE.
YOU GOT CASH?

32:54.931 --> 32:56.344
YEP, IN THE TRUCK.

32:56.344 --> 32:58.275
YOU JUST SAID THE RIGHT THING.
50 GRAND IT IS.

32:58.275 --> 32:59.689
-THANK YOU, SIR.
-LET'S GO DO SOME PAPERWORK.

32:59.689 --> 33:02.413
-ALL RIGHT.
-CASH ALWAYS WORKS.

33:02.413 --> 33:03.758
I MIGHT EVEN LEAVE IT
GREEN NOW.

33:03.758 --> 33:14.068
♪♪

33:14.068 --> 33:24.379
♪♪

33:24.379 --> 33:26.344
I DON'T THINK
THERE'S ANYTHING MORE MANLY

33:26.344 --> 33:27.448
THAN WHAT YOU JUST DID.

33:27.448 --> 33:28.793
ALL RIGHT.
DROP IT RIGHT THERE.

33:28.793 --> 33:30.275
OKAY.

33:30.275 --> 33:31.586
ALL RIGHT.
THAT WILL WORK.

33:31.586 --> 33:33.000
I'LL GET THE REAR END ON IT.
-ALL RIGHT.

33:33.000 --> 33:35.068
OR THE SPRING ON THE REAR END,
I SHOULD SAY.

33:35.068 --> 33:37.413
THIS IS A HEFTIER REAR END,
I'D SAY, FOR THE '33,

33:37.413 --> 33:39.137
BUT I NEED TO REPLACE
THE LEAF SPRING.

33:39.137 --> 33:40.275
IT'S A LITTLE BIT TRICKY.

33:40.275 --> 33:41.724
NOW, I'M GONNA PUT
THIS THING...

33:41.724 --> 33:44.103
IT'S CALLED A SPRING SPREADER,
THIS THING ON IT.

33:44.103 --> 33:45.655
IT'S ONE OF THOSE
SPECIALIZED TOOLS

33:45.655 --> 33:48.379
THAT YOU HAVE TO KIND OF COLLECT
IF YOU DO THESE CARS VERY OFTEN.

33:48.379 --> 33:51.620
IT'S REALLY TOUGH TO GET THE
SPRING ON IF YOU DON'T HAVE ONE.

33:51.620 --> 33:53.793
THIS IS REALLY THE ENTIRE
SUSPENSION FOR THE REAR END.

33:53.793 --> 33:55.724
THE WEIGHT OF THE TRUCK
BED RIDES ON THIS.

33:55.724 --> 33:57.103
THE SPRING IS KIND OF UNUSUAL

33:57.103 --> 33:59.206
BECAUSE IT'S PROBABLY
THE ONLY CAR EVER BUILT

33:59.206 --> 34:00.965
WITH A SPRING
THAT HAS A COMPOUND CURVE.

34:00.965 --> 34:03.068
IT CURVES THIS WAY
AND CURVES THAT WAY,

34:03.068 --> 34:07.482
WHICH IS PRETTY MUCH UNIQUE
TO A 1933 OR '34 FORD.

34:07.482 --> 34:09.793
WHY THEY DID THAT,
I STILL AM REALLY NOT SURE.

34:13.103 --> 34:14.586
HEY, JERMS,
I MIGHT NEED A HAND.

34:14.586 --> 34:16.448
Jeremy:
OOH, LET ME COME HELP.

34:16.448 --> 34:18.172
YOU WANT TO SLIDE THAT IN,
AND THEN WE'LL LIFT HER?

34:18.172 --> 34:19.931
YEAH.

34:19.931 --> 34:21.241
IT'S REALLY HEAVY.

34:21.241 --> 34:22.931
IS IT?
I GUESS I'LL HURRY.

34:22.931 --> 34:28.482
♪♪

34:28.482 --> 34:30.551
YEAH, SO WE'RE UP AGAINST
THE REAR END HOUSING RIGHT NOW.

34:30.551 --> 34:32.206
YEAH.

34:32.206 --> 34:33.758
LET ME TAP THAT THING BACK
AND JUST DON'T LET IT HIT YOU.

34:33.758 --> 34:35.413
INSTALLING THIS SPRING,
IT'S ACTUALLY

34:35.413 --> 34:36.689
A DANGEROUS PIECE OF BUSINESS.

34:36.689 --> 34:38.586
STAY CLEAR
BECAUSE THIS THING...

34:38.586 --> 34:40.586
IF IT SHOOTS OUT, IT WILL
PROBABLY GO ACROSS THE ROOM.

34:40.586 --> 34:41.827
IT'S GONNA TAKE YOUR [BLEEP]
ANKLES OUT, DUDE.

34:41.827 --> 34:43.000
YOU BETTER WATCH OUT.

34:43.000 --> 34:44.137
THERE IS A TREMENDOUS LOAD
ON THE SPRING

34:44.137 --> 34:45.344
WHEN YOU SPREAD IT OUT TO FIT.

34:45.344 --> 34:46.517
SERIOUSLY, IF THAT THING
SHOOTS OUT,

34:46.517 --> 34:48.310
IT'S GONNA KNOCK
YOUR HEAD OFF.

34:48.310 --> 34:50.620
THERE WE GO.
ALL RIGHT.

34:50.620 --> 34:52.172
OH, MY GOSH.
IT GOT HEAVIER.

34:52.172 --> 34:53.379
WHICH WAY
DO YOU WANT TO GO?

34:53.379 --> 34:54.379
-MAYBE YOUR WAY.
-THIS WAY?

34:54.379 --> 34:56.310
-YEAH.
-OH, THIS WAY.

34:56.310 --> 34:57.896
GOT IT?

34:57.896 --> 34:59.758
YOU'LL HAVE TO COME...

34:59.758 --> 35:00.862
BOOM.

35:00.862 --> 35:03.413
ALL RIGHT.
NOW WE NEED A FLOOR JACK.

35:04.413 --> 35:06.551
HERE, LET'S GET
THIS LINED UP.

35:06.551 --> 35:08.068
IT GOT A LITTLE BETTER.

35:08.068 --> 35:09.793
JUMP ON IT.

35:12.034 --> 35:13.586
-ALMOST.
-IT DEFINITELY MOVED.

35:13.586 --> 35:17.344
-TRY AGAIN?
-YEAH.

35:17.344 --> 35:18.448
I THINK THAT'S IT.

35:18.448 --> 35:21.344
THIS IS HOW ALL
THE BEST SHOPS DO IT.

35:21.344 --> 35:23.000
DAMN IT.
WHY DO I LISTEN TO YOU?

35:27.620 --> 35:28.758
WHOO!

35:28.758 --> 35:29.862
Narrator:
COMING UP ON "FAST N' LOUD..."

35:29.862 --> 35:31.034
Jason: WE DID ACTUALLY
HAVE AN ENGINE.

35:31.034 --> 35:33.517
Brian: THREE CARBURETORS ON IT,
FIN HEADS.

35:33.517 --> 35:35.103
WAIT.
THERE IS A SLIGHT ISSUE HERE.

35:35.103 --> 35:37.827
Narrator: RICHARD'S V-8 MOTOR
FOR THE '33 FORD FALLS FLAT.

35:37.827 --> 35:38.931
SO...

35:38.931 --> 35:40.275
THAT IS NOT GONNA FIT
THAT FRAME.

35:40.275 --> 35:41.724
Brian: OUR INITIAL PLAN WAS
TO TAKE IT OUT OF THE BOX

35:41.724 --> 35:43.137
AND BOLT IT INTO THE TRUCK.

35:43.137 --> 35:45.310
WE GOT TO TAKE THIS MOTOR
ALMOST COMPLETELY APART.

35:47.206 --> 35:48.379
-WHAT?
-I'M JUST TAKING A PICTURE.

35:48.379 --> 35:49.586
SMILE, AT LEAST.
-I DON'T LIKE PICTURES OF ME.

35:49.586 --> 35:52.379
I KNOW.
I SEE WHY.

35:52.379 --> 35:53.689
LOOK.
NO.

35:53.689 --> 35:54.862
LOOK.
NO.

35:54.862 --> 35:57.689
LOOK.
NO.

35:57.689 --> 35:59.068
YES, LOOK.

35:59.068 --> 36:00.827
NO. NO.

36:00.827 --> 36:02.103
NO, BECAUSE
I KNOW YOU'RE DOING

36:02.103 --> 36:03.379
SOMETHING TERRIBLE
WITH THAT PICTURE.

36:03.379 --> 36:05.344
I KNOW YOU.
NO, NO.

36:05.344 --> 36:06.586
I'M NOT DOING IT.

36:06.586 --> 36:08.379
WHAT ARE YOU WANT?
YOU [BLEEP]

36:08.379 --> 36:09.758
SUCH AN ASS.

36:09.758 --> 36:13.000
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU GOT THAT.

36:13.000 --> 36:15.655
YOU'RE AN ASS.
[ SIGHS ]

36:19.137 --> 36:21.103
Brian: HAVEN'T LOOKED
IN THE PARTS WASHER

36:21.103 --> 36:22.172
FOR, LIKE, THREE DAYS.

36:22.172 --> 36:23.413
IT'S STILL DIRTY.

36:23.413 --> 36:25.068
TRANSMISSION REPAIR
IS VERY IMPORTANT.

36:25.068 --> 36:26.793
REALLY, YOU SHOULD LEAVE IT
TO A PROFESSIONAL,

36:26.793 --> 36:28.413
AND AM I PROFESSIONAL
TRANSMISSION GUY?

36:28.413 --> 36:30.344
NO, BUT I'M GONNA PUT IT
TOGETHER ANYWAY.

36:32.862 --> 36:34.275
THIS IS ACTUALLY
THE TRANSMISSION

36:34.275 --> 36:35.793
WE'RE USING IN THIS TRUCK,

36:35.793 --> 36:38.068
AND IT LOOKS LIKE AN ANTIQUE
BECAUSE IT IS AN ANTIQUE.

36:38.068 --> 36:42.137
IT'S ONLY 6 YEARS NEWER THAN
THE TRUCK WE'RE PUTTING IT IN,

36:42.137 --> 36:43.655
SO 1939 TRANSMISSION.

36:43.655 --> 36:46.413
OUR TRUCK IS 1933, BUT THIS IS
A MUCH STRONGER TRANSMISSION

36:46.413 --> 36:48.827
THAN THE TRUCK WAS MADE WITH,
SO THIS IS A LITTLE BIT BETTER.

36:48.827 --> 36:50.103
IT'S AN UPGRADE.

36:50.103 --> 36:51.482
HOT RODDERS HAVE BEEN
DOING IT FOR YEARS,

36:51.482 --> 36:52.793
AND THAT'S WHAT WE NEED
TO USE IN OUR TRUCK,

36:52.793 --> 36:54.310
SO EVEN THOUGH WE'RE BUILDING
A SHOP TRUCK

36:54.310 --> 36:55.827
FOR RUNNING GARAGE ERRANDS
AND WHATNOT,

36:55.827 --> 36:56.931
WE'RE STILL MAKING A HOT ROD.

36:56.931 --> 36:58.413
IF IT HAS THE GAS MONKEY
NAME ON IT,

36:58.413 --> 36:59.931
YOU CAN BET IT'S GOING
TO BE A HOT ROD.

36:59.931 --> 37:01.931
WE HAVE TO PULL THE OLD BEARINGS
OFF OF ALL THE PARTS HERE

37:01.931 --> 37:03.517
AND PUT THE NEW BEARINGS ON,

37:03.517 --> 37:05.206
AND THEN I'LL ACTUALLY START
PUTTING IT IN THE CASE.

37:05.206 --> 37:06.551
WE'LL HAVE A TRANSMISSION.

37:06.551 --> 37:07.896
I'VE BEEN HOLDING
ONTO THIS '39 3-SPEED

37:07.896 --> 37:09.206
JUST FOR THIS PROJECT,
SO WHEN RICHARD

37:09.206 --> 37:11.206
BOUGHT THE TRUCK,
I MADE THAT PART OF THE DEAL.

37:11.206 --> 37:13.103
DOES THIS TURN YOU ON?

37:13.103 --> 37:15.068
NO ONE MAKES REPLACEMENT PARTS
FOR THESE OLD TRANSMISSIONS,

37:15.068 --> 37:18.896
SO I'VE HAD TO CLEAN UP
ALL THE ORIGINAL PARTS.

37:18.896 --> 37:20.172
WHEN I BROKE THE TRANSMISSION
DOWN,

37:20.172 --> 37:22.000
I TOOK SOME PICTURES
WITH MY PHONE.

37:22.000 --> 37:23.241
I'M USING THOSE TO MAKE SURE

37:23.241 --> 37:24.586
I GET IT PUT BACK TOGETHER
JUST RIGHT.

37:24.586 --> 37:26.586
SO THAT GOES LIKE THAT.

37:26.586 --> 37:29.034
Mike:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:29.034 --> 37:32.448
TRYING TO PUT THE TRANSMISSION
BACK TOGETHER.

37:32.448 --> 37:33.724
TRYING TO PUT THE TRANSMISSION
BACK TOGETHER...

37:33.724 --> 37:35.000
YEAH, TRYING.

37:35.000 --> 37:36.310
...OR PUTTING THE TRANSMISSION
BACK TOGETHER?

37:36.310 --> 37:37.482
-WELL, A LITTLE OF BOTH.
-YOU KNOW HOW IT IS?

37:37.482 --> 37:39.896
I THINK SO.
I'M GONNA FIND OUT.

37:39.896 --> 37:42.655
-IS THAT SUPPOSED TO BE THAT...
-OH, WAIT.

37:42.655 --> 37:44.034
THERE IS A TUBE MISSING
RIGHT THERE, THOUGH.

37:44.034 --> 37:45.724
YEAH, THERE'S A WHOLE TUBE
MISSING.

37:45.724 --> 37:48.275
YEAH, I DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE THAT.
I TOTALLY MISSED THAT.

37:48.275 --> 37:51.068
OKAY, WELL, I GOT TO GO FIND
ANOTHER CLUSTER GEAR NOW.

37:51.068 --> 37:52.344
WHERE WE GONNA
FIND THAT AT?

37:52.344 --> 37:53.758
YOU GOT ONE AT YOUR SHOP?
I BET YOU DO.

37:53.758 --> 37:55.000
I PROBABLY DO, YEAH.

37:55.000 --> 37:57.103
YOUR PILE OF JUNK.

37:57.103 --> 38:00.000
SEE, MY PILE OF JUNK
COMES IN HANDY, THOUGH.

38:00.000 --> 38:02.827
I'M NO MECHANIC, BUT YOU WOULD
THINK THAT SOMETHING

38:02.827 --> 38:04.379
THAT'S MISSING
A GIANT CHUNK OUT OF IT

38:04.379 --> 38:05.896
WOULD NOT BE GOOD
TO PUT BACK TOGETHER.

38:05.896 --> 38:07.103
IT'S PROBABLY BEEN
KIND OF NOISY,

38:07.103 --> 38:08.241
MISSING A TOOTH.

38:08.241 --> 38:09.310
-NOISY?
-YEAH.

38:09.310 --> 38:11.000
IF IT EVEN WORKED.IT WOULD WORK.

38:11.000 --> 38:12.448
IT WOULD JUST MAKE
A LOT OF NOISE.

38:12.448 --> 38:13.931
I'M SCARED IT'S EVEN
GONNA RUN NOW.

38:13.931 --> 38:15.344
GEEZ, LOUISE.

38:15.344 --> 38:16.931
Brian: WELL, THAT'S GONNA
SLOW ME DOWN A LITTLE BIT.

38:16.931 --> 38:18.448
I WAS JUST ABOUT READY TO PUT
THIS THING BACK TOGETHER,

38:18.448 --> 38:19.965
AND NOW I CAN'T.

38:19.965 --> 38:21.862
WELL, THE ONLY PLACE YOU'D GET
A CLUSTER GEAR

38:21.862 --> 38:23.000
FOR A '39 FORD TRANSMISSION

38:23.000 --> 38:24.655
IS FROM SOMEBODY
WHO HOARDS THAT CRAP.

38:24.655 --> 38:26.206
LUCKILY, I'M THAT GUY.

38:26.206 --> 38:28.758
I CAN'T GUARANTEE I'M GOING
TO ACTUALLY HAVE ONE.

38:28.758 --> 38:30.551
SO I GRAB JEREMY AND HEADED
TO MY SHOP.

38:30.551 --> 38:31.827
I FIGURE HE'S GOT A FRESH SET
OF EYES

38:31.827 --> 38:33.862
TO HELP ME SPOT
THE PART WE NEED.

38:33.862 --> 38:36.482
I KNEW THERE WOULD BE PROBLEMS
WE COULDN'T FORESEE.

38:36.482 --> 38:38.000
THERE ALWAYS ARE.
RIGHT.

38:38.000 --> 38:40.172
BESIDES, HE'S THE ONLY
THAT HASN'T BEEN TO MY PLACE

38:40.172 --> 38:41.793
AND DOESN'T GIVE ME
A HARD TIME ABOUT IT.

38:43.448 --> 38:45.379
DUDE.
I CAN TELL FROM HERE,

38:45.379 --> 38:47.275
THIS IS AS BAD
AS THEY SAID IT IS.

38:47.275 --> 38:50.896
THIS IS OLD STUFF
GALORE, MAN.

38:50.896 --> 38:52.689
YOU KNOW WHERE IT'S AT?
-NO.

38:52.689 --> 38:55.172
IS THERE WHERE STEERING COLUMNS
GO TO DIE?

38:55.172 --> 38:56.344
THAT'S VERY FUNNY.

38:56.344 --> 38:58.241
YOU HAVE, LIKE,
A WHOLE PLETHORA.

38:58.241 --> 38:59.448
HOLD ON.
THIS MIGHT BE IT.

38:59.448 --> 39:02.758
LET ME SEE
THE ONE YOU GOT.

39:02.758 --> 39:03.586
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

39:03.586 --> 39:04.724
Brian: SO THERE.

39:04.724 --> 39:06.655
MY STASH OF PARTS
JUST SAVED ME A TON TIME.

39:06.655 --> 39:08.275
YOU MIGHT THING THIS IS, LIKE,
A DIRTY SHOP,

39:08.275 --> 39:10.000
BUT IT JUST SAVED OUR ASS.

39:13.379 --> 39:14.862
Jason: LOOK WHAT I GOT.

39:14.862 --> 39:16.103
IS THAT
THE MYSTERIOUS ENGINE?

39:16.103 --> 39:17.448
THAT'S
THE MYSTERIOUS ENGINE.

39:17.448 --> 39:20.137
THIS IS AS MUCH OF IT
AS I'VE SEEN, SO...

39:20.137 --> 39:21.413
-THE BOX?
-YEAH.

39:21.413 --> 39:23.241
-THIS JUST LOOKS LIKE A BOX.
-BIG MOMENT.

39:23.241 --> 39:25.000
Brian: WHILE JEREMY AND I
WERE AT MY SHOP,

39:25.000 --> 39:26.068
THE GUYS KEPT ON TRUCKING.

39:26.068 --> 39:27.310
MIKE GOT THE CHASSIS PAINTED,

39:27.310 --> 39:28.931
SO NOW JEREMY CAN WORK
ON THE PEDAL ASSEMBLY,

39:28.931 --> 39:30.724
AND THAT MEANS SOON WE'LL
STABBING THE MOTOR IN THE TRUCK.

39:30.724 --> 39:32.172
SMALL-BLOCK.

39:32.172 --> 39:34.896
HEY, IT LOOKS GOOD ALREADY.IT'S A FLATHEAD.

39:34.896 --> 39:36.275
Brian: WHEN RICHARD WAS TRYING
TO GET ME TO SELL

39:36.275 --> 39:38.517
THIS TRUCK TO HIM,
HE THREW IN A LITTLE SWEETENER.

39:38.517 --> 39:39.965
I'VE GOT AN H&H FLATHEAD,

39:39.965 --> 39:42.000
ALL BUILT IN THE BOX,
BRAND-NEW.

39:42.000 --> 39:42.827
THAT'D BOLT RIGHT IN THERE,
JUST ABOUT.

39:42.827 --> 39:43.896
LET'S DO IT.

39:43.896 --> 39:45.103
I FIGURED HIS FLATHEAD V-8

39:45.103 --> 39:47.620
WOULD BE THE PERFECT MOTOR
FOR THIS BUILD.

39:47.620 --> 39:49.068
LOOK AT THAT.

39:49.068 --> 39:51.344
SO HE DID ACTUALLY
HAVE AN ENGINE.

39:51.344 --> 39:52.827
-YEP.
-IT'S GOT COBWEBS ON IT.

39:52.827 --> 39:56.379
THAT'S GOT THREE CARBURETORS
ON IT, FIN HEADS.

39:56.379 --> 39:57.931
WAIT.
-OFFENHAUSER.

39:57.931 --> 39:59.551
THERE IS
A SLIGHT ISSUE HERE.

39:59.551 --> 40:01.344
THIS ISN'T GONNA BOLT
INTO OUR TRUCK THE WAY IT IS.

40:01.344 --> 40:02.620
OH.

40:02.620 --> 40:05.620
THIS IS
A LATE-MODEL FLATHEAD.

40:05.620 --> 40:07.103
YOU KNOW, LIKE, THEY CHANGED
THEM BETWEEN '48 AND '49.

40:07.103 --> 40:08.620
THIS IS
A '49 TO '53 FLATHEAD,

40:08.620 --> 40:10.172
AND THAT IS NOT
GONNA FIT THAT FRAME

40:10.172 --> 40:12.517
WITHOUT
CHANGING SOME STUFF.

40:12.517 --> 40:13.931
OUR INITIAL PLAN WAS TO TAKE IT
OUT OF THE BOX

40:13.931 --> 40:15.241
AND BOLT IT INTO THE TRUCK.

40:15.241 --> 40:16.827
THAT'S WHAT RICHARD SAID
WE COULD DO.

40:16.827 --> 40:18.241
YOU'RE TALKING CHANGING THE
MOTOR OR CHANGING THE CHASSIS?

40:18.241 --> 40:19.862
WE GOT TO TAKE THIS MOTOR
ALMOST COMPLETELY APART.

40:19.862 --> 40:21.965
ALL THIS FRONT STUFF
ON THE ENGINE

40:21.965 --> 40:23.862
IS NOT REALLY GONNA WORK
WITH WHAT WE GOT HERE.

40:23.862 --> 40:26.241
WE NEED TO GET WITH CHAD
TO GET IMMEDIATELY HERE

40:26.241 --> 40:27.896
WHAT NEED
FOR THIS TO CONVERT IT.

40:27.896 --> 40:29.965
-IT TOO LONG OR SOMETHING?
-YEAH, IT WON'T FIT.

40:29.965 --> 40:31.482
THE WAY
THE MOTOR MOUNTS ARE,

40:31.482 --> 40:33.103
THEY'RE FOR
A LATER-MODEL FRAME.

40:33.103 --> 40:35.172
Man #4: WHAT A SWEET,
READY-TO-GO ENGINE, RICHARD.

40:35.172 --> 40:36.827
YOU AND I HAVE TO GET A PARTS
LIST TOGETHER

40:36.827 --> 40:39.517
BECAUSE THIS IS GOING
TO SLOW US DOWN.

40:39.517 --> 40:41.068
Brian: SO MUCH FOR BEING AHEAD
OF SCHEDULE.

40:41.068 --> 40:43.517
NOW WE'RE GONNA LOSE A WHOLE
DAY MODIFYING THE MOTOR,

40:43.517 --> 40:45.586
NOT TO MENTION HUNTING
DOWN REPLACEMENT PARTS.

40:45.586 --> 40:46.793
SO YOU KNOW WHAT?

40:46.793 --> 40:47.896
FOR ONCE, THIS ONE IS ON YOU,
RICHARD.

40:47.896 --> 40:49.620
LET'S GO, BASS.

40:53.241 --> 40:56.137
Narrator:
NEXT WEEK ON "FAST N' LOUD,"

40:56.137 --> 40:59.310
AS THE MONKEYS KEEP CRANKING
ON THE '33 FORD...

40:59.310 --> 41:00.586
UGH, I KNEW
THAT WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

41:00.586 --> 41:02.689
...RICHARD PUTS THEIR FEET
TO THE FIRE.

41:02.689 --> 41:04.655
I'M REALLY, REALLY FREAKING
PRESSED FOR TIME.

41:04.655 --> 41:07.172
WE'RE THE LAST PEOPLE THAT WANT
TO BE TAKING IT BACK APART.

41:07.172 --> 41:10.103
Narrator: ...AND MAY CAUSE THEM
TO BURN OUT.

41:10.103 --> 41:11.413
STOP.

41:11.413 --> 41:12.655
Brian: I'VE SEEN LOTS OF WEIRD
STUFF ON THESE CARS,

41:12.655 --> 41:13.758
AND THIS ONE IS
KIND OF BLOWING MY MIND.

41:13.758 --> 41:20.931
Narrator:
THEN RICHARD GOES FOR THE GOLD

41:20.931 --> 41:22.862
IN THE MONSTER JAM
WORLD FINALS...

41:22.862 --> 41:25.206
I WANT TO WIN. I WANT TO BE
FIRST PLACE EVERY TIME.

41:25.206 --> 41:27.689
Narrator: ...BY THROTTLING
SON-UVA DIGGER.

